name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above the ground north of the city.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 20 meters above the inside wall of West Midgaard.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 20 meters above the west gate of Midgaard.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Dwarven Drop Off
description:
This is where the dwarven mommies and daddies come to drop off their
annoying little brats.  You have the urge to leave.  There is a sign here.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above Wall Road.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Day Care Center
description:
You are in the north-east corner of the main part of the center.  Toys and
toddlers are all over the room.  There is a kitchen to the east.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above Wall Road.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: Day Care Center
description:
You are in the north-west corner of the main part of the center.  Toys and
toddlers are all over the room.  There is a bathroom to the west.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above the ground north of Midgaard.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: Day Care Center
description:
You are in the south-east corner of the main part of the center.  Toys and
toddlers are all over the room.  There is a playground to the east.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 20 meters above the magic shop.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above Main Street.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Void
description: You are floating in nothing.

name: Day Care Center
description:
You are in the south-west corner of the main part of the center.  Toys and
toddlers are all over the room.  There is a staircase to the west.

name: The Chat Room
description:
You are lounging in a quiet cosy parlour, warmed by a gentle magical fire
which twinkles happily in a warm fireplace.  This is one of the many rooms
where the heroes and gods come to socialize.  It is by far one of the most
comfortable!

name: On the spider web
description:
You are balancing carefully on the giant sticky threads that holds the giant
web in place.  To the south leads a strand to a cave-like structure made from
many layers of a spider web.  Another silky strand continues to the north.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

A floating sign says:

"Scubdu's Area--Tread carefully! Only high levels should attempt
this place. Leave messages on the board if you have problems."

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 20 meters above the Mage Guild Hall.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Limbo
description:
You are floating in a formless void, detached from all sensation of physical
matter, surrounded by swirling glowing light, which fades into the relative
darkness around you without any trace of edges or shadow.
There is a "No Tipping" notice pinned to the darkness.

name: Moses' Hangout
description:
You see here a cozy little room with a fireplace.  You can tell it is Moses'
room by the two stone tablets and a bible on a small ledge near the fireplace.
This room was designed for total relaxation.  You can watch television, listen
to the stereo, even soak in a hot tub.
There is a bell here for the butler.

name: On the spider web
description:
You are balancing carefully on the giant sticky threads that holds the giant
web in place.  To the north leads a strand to a cave-like structure made from
many layers of a spider web.

name: The Messy Bathroom
description:
You hold your nose as you realize you have made the worst mistake of your
life.  The air is rancid and the walls are stained.

name: City Entrance
description:
You are at the entrance to a small underground city. A great adamantite
gate lies open to the west allowing entrance into the city.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above Poor Alley.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: The Center of the Universe
description:
You are at the centre of the universe, everything is filled with bright
light in all colors. You feel time and space no longer exist here.
Exits fill the room in all 42 dimensions, leading everywhere.

name: City street
description:
You walk along a highly ornate street going north-south. A large gate
lies to the east while a building lies to the west.

name: The Staircase
description:
You stand on top of a staircase leading down, and wonder what mystery could
lie down under.  Beware!

name: On the spider web
description:
You are balancing carefully on the giant sticky threads that holds the giant
web in place.  To the east leads a strand to a cave-like structure made from
many layers of a spider web.

name: A Gravel Road in the Graveyard
description:
You are on a well-kept gravel road that leads north-south through the
graveyard.  On both sides of the road grow dark evergreen trees.  An iron
grate is to the north and narrow gravel paths lead east and west.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above the ground north of Midgaard.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: Valhalla
description:
This is the huge Hall of Valhalla, where the Gods rule supreme.  The
cavernous building stretches infinitely in all directions.  Valhalla
continues to the east, and the gods make their homes north and south of
the halls.  The golden gates are to the west.  You know not what lies
upward...

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: A long tunnel
description:
You encounter some rapids as you enter this tunnel cut out of
the mountains by the river.

name: The Playground
description: You are in the north-west corner of the playground.

name: City street
description: You walk along a highly ornate city street going north and west.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 20 meters above the bakery.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: On the spider web
description:
You are balancing carefully on the giant sticky threads that holds the giant
web in place. A single silky strand lead to the south, while another leads
off into the northern direction.

name: A Gravel Road in the Graveyard
description:
You are on a well-kept gravel road that leads north-south through the
graveyard.  On both sides of the road grow dark evergreen trees.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: Priscilla's Pleasure Palace
description:
As you look around you, you see the largest collection of erotic toys
in the world!!!  On a table in the middle of the room lies a book titled :
"All You Ever Wanted to Know About Sex..But Were Afraid to Ask"
There are things here that you never even imagined in your wildest dreams!

name: The edge of the forest
description:
You are standing at the eastern edge of a big forest.  To the east is the West
Gate of Midgaard and to the west is a narrow trail, leading in through the
forest.  A dimly lit path leads north.

name: The Playground
description: You are in the north-east corner of the playground.

name: A long tunnel
description: The tunnel branches off north.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above Main Street.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Webbed Entrance
description:
Sticky, sticky, sticky!  The ground is cluttered with leaves, decayed
remains of webbed crickets, beetle, rats, dogs (?), and even humans.
You begin to wonder about what lies ahead.  The air is damp here,
and even the little light that shines through the canopy seems
absorbed into the webbing.

name: City street
description:
You walk along a highly ornate city street going east-west. A large house
stands to the south.

name: A Gravel Road in the Graveyard
description:
You are on a well-kept gravel road that leads north-south through the
graveyard.  On both sides of the road grow dark evergreen trees.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: The Eye of the Hurricane
description:
The shrieking winds of a monstrous storm surround you, spinning you around
in an endless web of fury. But then, in the middle of turmoil, you find a
strange calm. You find yourself hovering in the calm eye of a hurricane. All
around you you can see the desruction caused by the powerful storm. White
hot flashes of lightning flicker from the depths of the hurricane.  But
everything is strangely peaceful in here, with the sun shining in from above
and a flock of birds winging across the sky.  You stretch out and relax, this
storm is going to be here a while.

name: The Playground
description: You are in the south-west corner of the playground.

name: A long tunnel
description: The tunnel branches off south.

name: The holy grove
description:
You are standing amidst the ancient oaks and poplars in the holy grove. You
can feel a strange sensation of contentedness and relief seeping through You,
as if great burdens have been lifted from Your shoulders. From here, friendly-
looking paths lead east and south.

name: A trail through the light forest
description:
You are on a trail leading through the forest.  To the east is the forest edge
and to the west, the trail leads further into the forest.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 20 meters above Armoury.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Webby Passage
description:
You find that footing here is very good, almost too good.  The
limbs are coated with cobwebs and seem unusually strong for tree
branches.  Paths lead in four directions.  The eastward path goes
down a bit.

name: 3rd House
description:
You stand inside the 3rd house of the city; it is fairly well decorated
by drow standards having a few statues, murals and such. A door leads to the
south.

name: Walking on the Moon
description:
The proud and lonely silence of Mare Imbrium surrounds you, as you gaze upon
the sterile splendor of the moon.  All around is the velvet curtain of night,
studded with a thousand gleaming jewels.  Below you hangs the beautiful
fields of Earth, looking fragile and far away, but full of hope.  A sense of
wistful regret touches you, as you think about what might have been, and what
will be.

name: A Gravel Road in the Graveyard
description:
You are on a well-kept gravel road that leads north-south through the
graveyard.  On both sides of the road grow dark evergreen trees.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: A long tunnel
description: The tunnel branches off to the south.

name: A trail through the light forest
description:
You are on a narrow trail leading east and west through the forest.  To the
west, the forest gradually becomes more dense.  A small forest path leads
south.

name: The holy grove
description:
You are standing amidst the ancient oaks and poplars in the holy grove. You
feel unusually happy here, as if great burdens have been lifted from Your
shoulders. From here, pleasant-looking paths lead east, west and south.

name: The Playground
description: You are in the south-east corner of the playground.

name: Wasp Hive
description:
Drones scuttle about in this room.  The cells on the walls
are honeycomb in shape and many of the maggots and wasps you see
have fang-marks on there bodies.  You sense some order in their markings.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above Poor Alley.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Throne Room
description:
The throne room of the 3rd house is about as decorated as the inner
courtyard except with a blood covered altar in the center of the room.

name: In front of the Chapel
description:
You are on an open space before a small chapel.  A gravel road leads north
through the graveyard and the chapel entrance is to the south.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: The Satin Memorial Reading Room
description:
Half read books lie everywhere: Yeats, Tennyson, Chandler, Barrie;
a battered paperback de Laclos; a dusty leather-bound Donne.  A
damp novel perches precariously on the edge of a large bathtub.
As your eyes travel beyond the steam rising to the air toward the
rose-brambled balcony railing, you notice a well-creased printout
of a poem sitting on a the velvet cushions of a rosewood chair
that has been set so as to see the stark black mountains
from one angle, or the wine-dark sea from another.

name: Muddy Path
description:
This section of the path is slowly being drowned by the nearby swamp to the
south, which is creeping slowly inland.  Several caved-in buildings sprawl
here, torn apart both by battle and the elements.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: A trail through the dense forest
description:
You are on a trail leading east and west through the dense forest.  To the
east, the forest gradually seems to become lighter.

name: An underground lake
description:
You are floating on a jet-black underground lake fed by dripping
water and lime from above. The tunnel continues to the east and the river
leads back west. To the north is a roughly-hewn hallway. There is also
a tunnel south.

name: A clearing in the woods
description:
You are standing in a clearing in the light woods. Somehow, this place
seems powerfully DIFFERENT from the rest of the forest, as if something is
severely strained in the fabric of reality here.  There is a small tablet
on one of the trees.

name: Entrance to the Mini-Maze
description:
You stand in the entrance to a small, but confusing maze.  You really hope
that you don't get lost.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 10 meters above the temple spire of Midgaard
It seems like you can see forever!

name: City street
description:
You walk along a highly ornate city street going east-west. To the north
is a large building.

name: Webby Passage
description:
Another webby passage, all sticky and wet.  Tiny ballooning
spiders fill the air.  It seems that these young ones are newborns.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  An old tomb is here.

name: A Sea Cave
description:
You are in a small cave in a cliff next to a deep green sea.  Fine
gold and pink sand blanket the floor.  Shells are scattered and strewn
about.  A blow hole in the roof of the cave allows beams of light to stream
in and illuminate the cave.  The wind blows outside the entrance, but
you are protected from the weather in your cozy cave.  The foamy surf
never seems to quite reach your feet.  Several boulders here have been
worn by time into a shape similar to a comfortable chair.

name: Swamp's Edge
description:
Briars and marsh plants stick to your boots and clothes, and clouds cover the
skies above the murky marsh, leaving the path before you dark and sinister.
You see some disturbances in the marsh, but after a few strangled screams,
the sounds stop.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: The holy grove
description:
You are standing amidst the ancient oaks and poplars in the holy grove. You
feel calm and relaxed here, as if great burdens have been lifted from Your
shoulders. From here, pleasant-looking paths lead east, north and south. To
the west, through the trees, You can see a faint trail leading towards the
eastern road.

name: A trail through the dense forest
description:
You are on a trail leading east and west through the dense forest.  To the
west, the trees are so huge and their crowns so dense that forest remains in
total darkness.  A small path leads south through the trees.

name: A long narrow tunnel
description: The tunnel rises sharply to the east.

name: Beneath the Busy Path
description:
You hear the sounds of crawling arachnids above.  The rhythms of
the footsteps suggest a primitive order in their movement.  The light
seems brighter upwards.

name: Mini-Maze
description: You are in a small passage that looks just like every other one.

name: City street
description:
You walk along a highly ornate city street leading north and east. To the
south is an extremely large house.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above the Temple Square.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: Inside the Chapel
description:
You are in a small, dark chapel.  The dark brown glass in the tiny windows
do not let much light through.  A few rows of worn wooden benches stand here.

name: The Tower Gates
description:
You are at the entrance to a tall tower.  Lightning flashes periodically and
it is raining.  You think it might be a good idea to turn back into the grove.

name: Marshy Forest
description:
This area is by no means a forest, but for those who dwell in these sparse
trees it is one.  Occasionally you see a whole humanoid form floating face down
in the water, but mostly you only find pieces.  You hear a loud bellow in the
distance.  And feel fear creep into your heart.

name: The Archmage's Workroom
description:
This well-lit room is absolutely filled with clutter -- enchanting gear,
reagents, spell components, ancient tomes, scrolls, braziers, exotic incense
and countless other tools of the magical trade, all jumbled together with
seemingly no attention paid to organization.  You have no doubts that Alander
can find whatever he needs without delay, however.  A heavy oak door stands
barred to the south, to discourage idle visitors, and Alander's quarters
are east.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: The sacred glade
description:
You are standing in the middle of the sacred glades, where the citizens of
Midgaard come to celebrate the spring, where farmers give thanks for bountiful
harvest in the fall, and where lovers stroll in summer. You feel seasons of
remembered happiness and joy taking Your sorrows and worries away from You,
leaving You calm and invigorated, ready for the world. Paths lead into the
holy grove to the east, north and west, while to the south a wide, sunny field
slopes down to a sparkling lake.  Above you is a strange shimmering, almost
like something from another world....

name: A wide tunnel
description:
The tunnel continues east and west. To the east the tunnel dives
down into a bright light.

name: A small path in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The crowns of the
old trees leave the forest in an unreal twilight illumination.  The path
continues north and south.

name: On the Busy Path
description:
Spiders, spiders, everywhere!  It is almost ant-like in efficiency
with one big difference.  The spiders here are carrying ant-corpses,
as well as rats, wolves, and humans.

name: 2nd House
description:
You stand inside the 2nd house of the city. The room is highly decorated
with statues of spiders and murals everywhere.

name: Inside a Tavern
description:
You are inside a dimly-lit room.  The atmosphere makes you feel uncomfortable.
In front of you stands a mysterious gypsy.  She whispers 'Your fate and
destiny lie beyond this world.'  You are still wondering what she means when
you suddenly notice the crystal ball ... it glows fiercely and displays the
Universe!

name: Mini-Maze
description: You are in a small passage that looks just like every other one.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above Market Square.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Path to Dwarven Village
description:
All around you are the mountains of the southern range, home of dwarves and
giants.  You can climb back down the mountains to the west and leave these
realms, or seek riches in the northern mineshafts.  A dirt road leads south,
towards a small building.  You can hear crying and shrieking coming from it.

name: Stairwell into Darkness
description: You sense even more danger coming from below but are urged onward ...

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads north and west.  An old tomb is here.

name: An ominous storm cloud.
description:
You find yourself in a storm.  Lightning flashes and thunder
crashes, making you wish you were dry and warm.

name: The Foyer
description:
This is the entrance to the Tower.  The hallway continues to the north,
leading towards a staircase.  You notice a grim painting on the wall,  and
quickly look away.

name: On a hill.
description:
You stand atop a hill on the northwestern side of the evil swamp. Dark
clouds whip around you and the wind raises its voice and assails you.

name: Office
description:
The first thing you notice about this office is the floor; it
is a black & white checkerboard pattern, with 8 squares to a side.  The
south wall is a HUGE picture window that produces a magnificent view of
the land.  In front of the window is a large desk.  Completely covering
the east wall is a bookshelf, that is crammed full.  In the northwest
corner, you notice a statue.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: Cave-in
description:
You stand at the edge of a large pile of rubble created from the last
rockslide.

name: The holy grove
description:
You are standing amidst the ancient oaks and poplars in the holy grove. You
can feel a strange sensation of joy and calm seeping through You, as if great
burdens have been lifted from Your shoulders. To the south, You glimpse an open
area through the trees, while paths lead away north and west.

name: North entrance to the catacombs
description:
You are almost surprised to see a tunnel leading off to the south
into utter darkness.  The floorboards above you haven't been moved
in a long time, yet there is life down here.  A beam of light from
the opening above you falls upon a message scrawled on the wall here.

The message reads:
Adventure for the strong yet calculating
Death for the weak and shallow
Treasure for the smart and lucky
Death for the stupid and accursed

An ancient Glyph above the entrance keeps monsters from wandering up
from the catacombs.

name: A small path in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The crowns of the
old trees leave the forest in an unreal twilight illumination.  The path
continues north and east.

name: On the Busy Path
description:
Spiders, spiders, everywhere!  It is almost ant-like in efficiency
with one big difference.  The spiders here are carrying ant-corpses,
as well as cats, wolves, and humans.

name: Throne Room
description:
The throne room of the 2nd house is just a little more decorative than
the inner courtyard having an altar in the center of the room.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above Market and Commons.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Mini-Maze
description: You are in a small passage that looks just like every other one.

name: Path, base of mountain
description:
Now you are at the bottom of a rugged mountain.  The forest around you is
very dense, and it seems very dark to the north.

name: Inside the Crystal Ball
description:
You have touched the crystal ball and find that you have gone inside it:
a world of stars and wonders!  As you look back you figure out there is no
choice but to go forward.

name: The Acolyte's Bedroom
description:
This is why you were not welcomed at the entrance by the tomb's faithful
servants ... blood and gore is ankle deep in here.
Oh NO! the door shut behind you!  It's a trap!
A bloodied corpse of an acolyte is lying here ...
A bloodied corpse of an acolyte is lying here ...
A bloodied corpse of an acolyte is lying here ...

name: High and perilous cliff
description:
You are on a high and rocky cliff.  To the west you see a huge
ominous storm cloud moving this way.  You might want to take cover
before the storm hits.  You think that there is a narrow trail
leading to the south.

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: Hallway
description:
This hallway seems to stretch on forever.  You notice a stairway in
the distance.

name: An Oozing Bog
description:
You stand in an oozing quagmire.  A creaking beat fills the air,
accompanied by groans and soughing of the air.  Several large winged
beasts flap over you and send chilling glares your way.  You feel out
of place, and feel that the occupants of this realm will soon
have you for a feast.

name: Arena of Judgement
description:
The scene lain before you is one that gives you the feeling of being placed
under a higher authority.  The jury is out.  A statue of Pontius Pilate is
in the aft of the Arena.  Staring balefully, the statue faces a distant
hillside where many aged crosses still stand.  The Arena is set in a wide
pit-like field of trampled bloodstained grass, and is guarded by high walls
of veinous marble.  A bloodstone seat awaits the true paragon of Romanity.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: At the foot of the rubble
description:
You are at the bottom of a large pile of rubble. A tunnel branches
off to the north and east.

name: The holy grove
description:
You are standing amidst the tall, majestic trees in the southern end of the
holy grove. Paths lead north and east. To the east, You can see a wide, open
field, sloping gently down towards a bright, glittering lake. Somehow, here
you feel an inexplicable happiness, as if the world's troubles no longer
really matter to you.

name: An intersection in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The crowns of the
old trees leave the forest in an unreal twilight illumination.  The forest
gradually lightens to the east.  Paths lead east, west and south.

name: On the Busy Path
description:
Spiders, spiders, everywhere!  It is almost ant-like in efficiency
with one big difference.  The spiders here are carrying ant-corpses,
as well as cats, dogs, and humans.

name: Entrance to Gnome Village
description:
You stand on a dusty path that leads north and east.  To the east you hear
the sounds of a small village.

name: Main Gate
description:
You are at the entrance to the 1st house of the city. A large gate, almost
as big and elegant as the one at the entrance to the city, stands here.

name: North/south tunnel
description:
This part of the catacombs looked roughly hewn and man-made. There is
a large cross painted on the floor of the tunnel.To the south it seems
maybe a bit lighter for some odd reason.  To the north a ray of light
comes in from a hole in the ceiling.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above ground, overlooking the Common Square.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Path, middle of mountain
description:
Standing on the middle of the mountain, you can easily see the turning
point to the south, and the top of the mountain is very near to the north.

name: Mini-Maze
description: You are in a small passage that looks just like every other one.

name: Inside the Galaxy
description:
You are now inside the galaxy, around you you see stars and nebulae smiling
at your presence, and comets and meteors wandering around you.  You realize
that this world may not be the true galaxy after all, but just another
fantasy zone.  Exits lie virtually in all directions.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads east and south.  An old tomb is here.

name: An Oozing Bog
description:
The ground here is soft and oozing.  You feel slimy water seeping into your
boots.  Better stop and check for leeches when you get out of here.

name: Narrow rocky trail.
description:
A narrow trail leads down towards the mountain and north toward the
cliff.  It seems to fade in and out as it winds up the hill.
Obviously, it has not been maintained in years.

name: Hallway
description: You trudge down the hallway.  You notice doors to the east and west.

name: The Realm of the Dead
description:
You are standing on an immense, grey stone floor that stretches as far as you
can see in all directions.  Rough winds plunging from the dark, starless sky
tear savagely at your fragile body.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: Cave entrance
description:
You stand in the middle of a large and beautiful cave. A path leads
deeper into the darkness.

name: A Split in the Path
description:
As always, there is a split in the road.  One road is strewn
with cricket feelers.  The other is well-kept and suitable for smooth
travelling.  The webbing that was prevalent in earlier rooms is almost
non-existent now.

name: The forest clearing
description:
You are in a clearing in the forest.  Lots of fresh stumps of varying sizes
protrude from the ground and heavy logs are stacked neatly in a big pile
supported by stakes set into the ground.  Paths lead north, east and west.

name: The sunny field
description:
You are standing in the middle of a wide, summery, sunlit field. There is a
fragrance of spring in the air, a sound of summer and a feeling of eternal
Saturday afternoon. To the south is a clear, sparkling lake, and to the north
and west is the holy grove. In the wood's edge, to the east, is a stately man-
sion, shimmering softly through the colors of the rainbow. You feel as if You
could spend the rest of your life here, lying on your back and looking at the
patterns of the clouds as they gently drift across the sky.

name: Weapon training area
description:
This is a place to keep up on there weapon skills.  Much of the
equipment looks old and worn but upon further inspection seems quite
sturdy in fact.

name: A Dusty Path
description:
This is a path leading into the village.  It continues east and west and
there is a small house to the north.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above the ground just north of Midgaard.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: 1st House
description:
You stand in the inner courtyard of the 1st and largest house in the city.
The room is extremely large and decorative. Mural and paintings hang on the
walls depicting some battles and a spider queen.

name: Top of mountain
description:
You are now on the top of the mountain.  To the south you see a path
leading down the mountain.  To the east and west you see entrances to
what seems like mines.

name: On an InterGalactic Walkway
description:
You are on a well-paved path which seems that it was made deliberately for
visitors like you.  The walkway continues north and a small exit lies west.

name: End of the Mini-Maze
description:
You stand at the end of your journey.  There is a big sign here and you had
better read it!

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: Swamp Thing's Lair
description:
A horrible swamp thing resides here.  Mutilated corpses suffuse the air with
the overwhelming stench of putrid flesh.

name: Small valley.
description:
You are in a lush valley full of trees and other vegetation and the
odd carcass or two.  The trail leads south and it leads up.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: Nursery
description:
It looks like a tornado has been through here.  Toys are scattered everywhere,
and a small group of dragon hatchlings are fighting over a bone.

name: Asgard
description:
You stand on a huge expanse of glass.  Below you are clouds and the
pains of mortality.  As you stand in Asgard, home of the bravest of the
brave, you are frozen in awe of the power held within these walls.  A
huge mansion lies to the east beyond a set of magnificent golden doors.

name: Giant cave
description:
This cavern overwhelms you. The walls and ceiling seem miles away.
Bones of previous adventurers lie strewn on the cavern floor.

name: Outside a small cabin in the forest
description:
You are outside a small cabin built entirely from heavy logs.  There is a
wooden door to the north and small paths lead west and south through the trees.

name: Fuzzy Tree Limb
description:
You are on a "fuzzy" tree limb.  Interesting, since the branches
seem to have "hairs" sprouting from its bark.  As you look
closer you see millions of aphids covering each limb.

name: Prayer training area
description:
The templar's curious mix of religion and fighting is evident here.
A central painting depicts a cross composed of swords.  The elders
teach the ancient art of prayer to the young pages.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above the west gate of Midgaard.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The croquet lawn
description:
You are standing on a immaculately manicured green lawn, the kind you only
get after 200 years of meticulous work. There is a winding stone path leading
from the wood's edge to the north, to the softly shimmering, rainbow-colored
mansion to the south. This place enjoys a perpetual cool, sunny summers after-
noon.

name: Throne Room
description:
The throne room of the 1st house is in one word...awesome. It is so
horrifying it is almost beautiful.

name: A Road in the Village
description:
This road runs north and south through the center of the village.  There
are a few people moving around, but not many.

name: Narrow Path
description:
This is a narrow path leading to the Dwarven Kingdom.  It looks less
travelled than the others, and it is very creepy.  The path opens up
to the south, and continues to the north.

name: End of the InterGalactic Walkway
description:
You notice the walkway has come to an abrupt end and you wonder why. You see
that there is still a small path which leads north and one to the west.
To the east lies a bridge.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads north and east.  A small shed is to the west.

name: The Grand Hall of Kings
description:
You are at the west end of the Grand Hall of Kings.  There is a doorway to the
south with something strange written above it.  Also on the floor are dried
blood stains, but their color seems a little wrong.

name: Storage Room
description: This room is covered with dust, it looks as if no one has been here in ages.

name: The Room of Lost Souls
description:
This is the room full of souls that never made it to Asgard.  They are
trapped here eternally, left to wander about in misery.  They were infidels
and cowards.  Their cries of misery send a shiver down your spine.

name: Messy Kitchen
description:
You stand in the kitchen and eating area of the day care center.  Pots and
pans are everywhere, while the toddlers continue to create chaos.

name: Small valley.
description:
You are in a lush valley full of trees and other vegetation and the
odd carcass or three.  The trail leads north and it leads down into
a crevasse.

name: Narrow bend
description: The tunnel turns to the south and west.

name: Pool of Quick Sand
description:
You stand by a large oozing pool of quick sand.  Luckily only a complete
klutz could not avoid it.  Dancing lights fly about you and one seems to
be taunting you towards the pool.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: Inside the cabin
description:
You are inside a small one-room cabin made entirely from heavy logs.  It is
very sparsely furnished, containing only most basic housekeeping equipment,
such as a bed, a chair and a table.

name: Junction of hallways
description:
Training facilities are evident to the west. To the south lies a hallway
which has doors every couple of feet, looks like living quarters of some
sort.  To the east the tunnel leads back into the natural catacombs.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above west gate of Midgaard.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Main Chamber
description:
This is the council chamber for the Matron Mother herself. A huge table
and chairs surrounding it sits in the center of the room.

name: A Dusty Path
description:
You are on a dusty path on the far side of the village.  Houses are to the
north and south, while the path continues east.  There is a sign here.

name: Entrance to Mountain
description:
Here is an entrance to the mountain.  The door looks very well built,
and you can hear noise coming from within.

name: The foyer
description:
You are standing in the foyer of Dragon's mansion. The wide double door to
the croquet lawn is to the north, flanked by large windows. The walls are
panelled in oak and hung with strange paintings.  There is door in the south
wall.

name: Tree Trunk
description:
You feel that you can rest here safely.  There is evidence of
webbing here, but it is of a finer quality.

name: At the Undeveloped Part of the Galaxy
description:
This place looks deserted, covered with space debris.  Not a sign of life
is around.

name: In a shed on the Graveyard
description:
You are in a small shed that looks as if it is used to store all sorts of
gardening equipment.  The only exit appears to be through a door to the east.

name: The Shrine of Shohan
description:
BLOOD EVERYWHERE!
The walls are coated with blood, bits of bloody flesh lie at your feet,
and torn clothing is scattered about.  It wouldn't disturb you in the least
except that it is all FRESH!  What ever used to pass as an altar here,
lies overturned and smashed.  Doors lead to the south and to the north.

name: End of the Hallway
description:
You have finally reached the end of the hallway.  A huge staircase leads up.
You see a sign at the base of the staircase.

name: The End?
description:
You have reached the final lair.  It is dominated by a huge five headed
dragon (actually an overgrown brat with a Halloween mask).

name: Deep, slippery crevice.
description:
The crevice is deep and a little dim and it is hard to make your
way around.  A mist makes everything a little damp and slippery.
Better take your time climbing through here.

name: A Dark Pool.
description:
You stand beside a large dark pond.  The water boils not with heat, but with
motion, as if it is alive.  A creaking beat pulses through the air, leaving
you with a cold sweat and fear in your heart.

name: Large cave
description: You are standing in a large cave. Many furs are spread out on the floor.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: A small path through the light forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the forest.  The trees are tall and
slender.  Paths lead north and south.

name: Head of the Rainbow Bridge
description:
Standing on the mortal end of the Rainbow Bridge, the bridge arches up
before you and seems to disappear into the clouds.  You wonder if it is
wise to venture upward into the realm of the gods.  But it seems so calm
and peaceful here that it would be a shame to leave...

name: Hallway
description:
The hallway takes on a more indoor look to the west.  To the east it
looks awfully dark.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above wall road.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: A Road in the Village
description:
This road runs north and south through the center of the village.  There
are a few people moving around, but not many.

name: Bend in Narrow Path
description:
This is a narrow path that bends to the east here.  The trees hang over
the path, and it is very overgrown.  The narrow path continues to the
south and to the east.

name: The hallway
description:
You are in the north end of a connecting hallway, tastefully decorated with
oak paneling and the coat-of-arms of various famous nobles hung on the walls.
The hallway leads south, and there is a door in the eastern wall.

name: City street
description: You walk along a highly ornate city street leading north-south and east.

name: Tree Lair Entrance
description:
It seems the inhabitant of this place does not web her
victims, as evidenced by the remains before you.  The area
is cluttered with desiccated corpses, apparently bitten
but unwebbed, and drained of their life juices.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads south and west.  An old tomb is here.

name: The Tomb of Shohan
description:
Once beautiful, this place has been turned into a slaughterhouse by the hands
of evil beings ... even more blood and dead, rotting flesh.  This place looks
like the feeding grounds of beasts and monsters.  The overturned sarcophagus
of the once powerful King Shohan lies here.  A door leads to the north and a
doorway has been hewn to the east.

name: On the Bridge of Stars
description:
This bridge has been made by the stars to honour their ancestors.  The
bridge itself shines brightly and makes you feel that you are walking on
a path of light.  An entrance to an ancient building lies north and to
the east lies the Milky Way.

name: Gloomy Path Through the Marsh.
description:
To the north lies a hill, shrouded in dark clouds, and to the south lies
a huge patch of vegetation.  You sense an evil presence and notice
a beast flying overhead to the south east, towards what looks to be a
huge fortress, half buried in the marsh.

name: Guardian's Room
description:
You climb down the rickety stairs and find yourself face to face with a
gargantuan hydra.  How fast can you climb UP stairs?

name: Incredibly slippery crevice.
description:
The crevice is getting more and more slippery.  You are getting
incredibly nervous and want to turn back.  To the east is the
crevice and trail you were following.  Below, you can just see the
edge of a cliff through the mist.  There is no trail leading there,
just a smooth, flat, dew-covered rock that almost resembles a
slide ...

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: Damp hallway
description: The walls here are extremely damp, as well as the floor.

name: An intersection in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The crowns of the
old trees leave the forest floor in an unreal twilight illumination.  Paths
lead north, east and south.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above wall road.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Entrance of Valhalla
description:
The huge ornate entrance of Valhalla is before you.  It seems as though
atleast eight-hundred soldiers could walk abreast of one another through
these doors. You stare in awe at the sparkling mansion before you.  You
wonder what secrets are held behind these doors and long to hear the stories
of bravery and glory that you know are kept within the walls of Valhalla.

name: A Road in the Village
description:
This road runs north and south through the center of the village.  There
are a few people moving around, but not many.

name: Intersection
description:
The tunnel continues to the north and the south, becoming less hewn and
more natural to the south.  A passageway lined with paneling leads west.

name: City street
description:
You walk along a highly ornate city street leading south. A building is
to the west.

name: Narrow path
description: This path is very narrow, and it continues to the north and west.

name: Wolf Spider Lair
description:
Very dark, as all lairs of spiders are.  Not much of furnishings
save an exit.  The wolf spider keeps no corpses here, but rather
throws them out at her leisure.

name: The blue room
description:
You are in the blue room, one of the guest rooms in Dragon's mansion. The
walls are (surprise!) blue, and the rest of the room is decorated in similar
shades, producing a very nice, cool effect. There is a large bed and a
matching set of sofas, easy-chairs and a coffee table. Through the venetian
blinds in front of the large east window you can see the edge of the grove.

name: On the Bridge of Nebulae
description:
This bridge, like the other, was made as a memorial.  The nebulae had to
make one just to show that they are as capable as the stars.  North lies
a throne room.

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: Steep mountainside.
description:
From here, you can see forever.  Clouds, birds, the forest.
Midgaard is far, far to the west.  What a postcard perfect view!

name: Cloud of Darkness.
description:
As you travel through this cloud of darkness, a fear such as you have never
known before assails you.

name: The Treasure Room
description:
You have made it past the hydra into the vault.  You are astounded by
the treasure here.  Not only are you now rich, you can probably rest here
safely.  The west wall seems to have a large door made entirely of ruby.

name: Underground pool
description: You are wading in a knee deep pool of lime-water.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: A small path in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The crowns of the
old trees leave the forest in an unreal twilight illumination.  The path
continues east and west.

name: Valhalla
description:
You are standing in the halls of Valhalla.  Pictures of Odin, Thor, Tyr,
Loki, Freyr, Feyja, and Balder line the walls.  The cavernous hall extends
to the east and west.  Rooms belonging to the gods lie to the north and
south.  There appears to be an exit above you, but you do not know what is
up there...

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above the ground north of Midgaard.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Cleric Academy
description: This is the most lavish of the academies being that it is for the clerics.

name: A Road in the Village
description:
This road runs north and south through the center of the village.  There
are a few people moving around, but not many.

name: Pages' sleeping quarters
description:
Several bunk beds are lined up across the room.  It looks rather spartan
and there is little evidence of toys or games.  Most of the desks are
filled with books and papers of little interest.

name: Narrow north-south path
description:
This path leads to the north and south.  To the north you can see a
door, and to the south the path continues.

name: The Webless Path
description:
Strange.  No webbing here.  In fact, no sounds whatsoever.
The path continues northward, where you find that you may have to
tightrope your way across a ravine.

name: The hallway
description:
You are standing in the south end of the hallway. There are doors in the
elegant oak-panelled walls to the south, east and west. Many different
coat-of-arms adorn the walls here.

name: The Throne Room of the Nebula King
description:
You can only faintly make out that it is a throne room as it is too
dark in here.  In the middle is an empty throne.  You wonder where
the King has gone, maybe he is hiding from you?

name: The Second Floor
description:
You have made it up to the second floor.  You hear hissing and see several
dragon men rushing you.  You wonder how long you will be staying here.

name: Steep mountainside.
description:
From here, you can see forever.  Clouds, birds, the forest.
Midgaard is far, far to the west.  What a postcard perfect view!

name: Entrance to the Lower Chambers
description:
You can tell that this area wasn't a part of the original construction.
The walls have been hewn by a mighty force look as though they were CLAWED.
The passage slopes upward here and also continues to the north.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads north and south.  An old tomb is here.

name: Near Vegetation from Hell.
description:
You stand near some of the strangest plant life you have ever seen, a mixture
of tumescent vegetables, evil-smelling fruit trees, and malignant ferns.

name: Damp hallway
description:
The walls of the tunnel are extremely damp here. You hear the faint
sound of running water to the south.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: An intersection in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The forest gradually
lightens to the north.  Paths lead north, east and west.

name: Valhalla
description:
You are standing in the halls of Valhalla.  Tapestries of the gods line
the walls.  A statue of Odin is here.  The halls continue to the east and
west, and there are doors to the north and south of you.  There is some
sort of exit above you, but you do not know where it leads...

name: Templar Knights sleeping quarters
description:
This is a huge room which is filled wall to wall with beds. Apparently
all the low level knights all sleep in this one room.  A door on the
south wall is labelled "Elders only!".

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above the magic shop.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Door to Kingdom
description:
Here the path turns to the west.  You can see a door in front of you,
and the path continues to the west and south.

name: A Road in the Village
description:
This road runs north and south through the center of the village.  There
are a few people moving around, but not many.

name: City street
description:
You walk along a highly ornate city street going east-west. To the north
is a giant temple.

name: Above the Ravine
description:
Stranger still.  Your feet get a real firm grip on the spiderline.
You are above a deep ravine.  This line connects you between two trees.
Below you can see a prismatic web with lots of animal bones caught in it:
some bear and small deer bones in fact.  No human skeletons are visible
(yet).

name: The red room
description:
You are in the red room, one of the guest rooms in Dragon's mansion. The
walls are wallpapered a deep warm red, and dark mahogany panelling nicely com-
plements them. There is a large, warm waterbed and a sofa group in dark wood
with leather upholstery, including a coffee table. Heavy brown curtains are
pulled away from the wide windows, to reveal a nice view towards the grove.

name: At the Start of the Milky Way
description:
It is here that the famous old Milky Way starts flowing.  You are surrounded
by streams of mist the moment you tread on it.  You can't see well in
here ... luckily you haven't fallen yet!

name: The Court
description:
You have entered what seems to be a large court.  The people guarding it
don't seem happy to see you ...

name: Treacherous Cliff.
description:
The cliff is rocky and difficult to negotiate.  One wrong slip and
you could fall and break a leg or impale yourself or something else
nasty.

name: Narrow crawlway
description:
This crawlway is just big enough for a human to crawl through or a
halfling to walk through.

name: The Grand Hall of Kings
description:
This is the western wing of the Grand Hall of Kings.  Your only exits are to
the east and west in this gloomy hallway.

name: By the Monolith.
description:
You are standing near a monolith which protrudes some 20 feet from the
marsh into the air.  Its black obsidian surface shines darkly in the
strange, almost unearthly light that enters through the clouds above.

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: Valhalla
description:
You have reached the end of the halls of Valhalla.  There are heavy doors
on 3 walls.  They lead into the rooms of the gods.  The hall goes back to
the west, and there is some sort of an exit above you.  Torches sputter
softly and the scent of incense is strong here.

name: A small path in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The crowns of the
old trees leave the forest in an unreal twilight illumination.  The path
continues south and west.

name: N/S hallway
description:
The hallway leads north an south.  A door leads to a templar's room to
the east.  The decoration looks rather sparse here.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above main street.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Rainbow Web
description:
This is the rainbow web--each strand, each link, a hue of violently
sharp colors and contrasts.  The resident here seems to have a command
of light as well.

name: Path to the Castle
description:
You are on a path that will eventually lead to the castle.  It
continues north to the castle, and there is a door on the western wall.

name: Hall O' Pleasure
description:
You stop dead in your tracks as you enter this ornately decorated room - it
is populated with the king's harem.

name: The kitchen
description:
You are standing in the middle of Dragon's kitchen. Contrary to popular
belief, He *doesn't* eat virgins, which is amply demonstrated by the large
variety of foodstuffs found here on the shelves. There are numerous cans of
tomatoes, peas, corn etc., vines of garlic, a *Huge* array of small spice jars
along several shelves and a large combo refrigerator/freezer. A big oven and
stove is lurking in a corner. There is some proof here that Dragon is a less
than meticulous housekeeper... There are doors to the north and west.

name: Along the Milky Way
description:
You are still travelling inside this path of mist.  You notice a small
opening to the east.

name: Warrior's Academy
description: This looks more like a barracks than a school.

name: A Small Gnome House
description:
This is a small suburban house made from quality wood.  You can see the
expert workmanship that went into making it, but it lacks creativity.

name: Cliff Face.
description:
You are more than a little nervous climbing on this almost vertical
cliff face.  You miraculously find places to grab onto and little
ledges to rest on.  You see a small cave here.

name: Murky Bog.
description:
A murky bog surrounds you.  To the east a black monolith juts forth from the
ground.  Far to the north lies a huge pool of quicksand.  Snarls can be heard
echoing as if from a great distance.

name: The Shrine of Cristis
description:
Different than the rest, this place has not been desecrated.  An altar still
stands here and the walls show scenes from the life of Cristis the Kind,
a ruler of the outlying regions west of Midgaard.  There is a stone staircase
leading down.  The Ghost of Cristis the Kind stands here.

name: Large cavern
description:
You have entered a very large cavern. The rock formations would amaze
almost any dwarf.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads north and east.  An old tomb is here.

name: On the Rainbow Bridge
description:
You have reached the center of the Rainbow Bridge.  Clouds and mist swirl
around your feet.  The view from here is incredible.  It is little wonder
that the heavens were saved for the gods personal pleasures.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above the mage guild.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: A Middle-aged templar's room
description:
This is a room furnished in a room becoming a low level templar scribe.
No real amenities but better than a communal sleeping quarters. As far
as you can tell he would be a rank equivalent to a Sargeant.

name: A small path in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The crowns of the
old trees leave the forest in an unreal twilight illumination.  The path
continues north and south.

name: The Web Forest
description:
The trees here take on a different appearance--they are not trees
anymore, but disjointed make-shift silken made shafts, sticky to the touch,
and webby in texture.  This is another world it would appear.

name: Still on the path to the Castle
description:
You are still on the path to the castle, or back to the
Dwarven village, whichever way you wish to go.  The path
continues to the north and south.

name: The Court
description: You are continuing down the hall.  To the east and west you see ornate doors.

name: The ballroom
description:
You are standing in the middle of a vast palisander floor. This is where
Dragon entertains large number of guests, but the cloth-covered chairs
standing forlornly in a corner suggests that this does not happen often.
There are doors in the south and east walls, while to the west there is a
short corridor to the greenhouse.

name: At the End of the Milky Way
description:
Just as you started enjoying this journey inside the mist, you have come to
the end of it.  West leads to a bridge and east leads to somewhere else.

name: Entrance to the Temple of Lloth
description:
The temple is the largest building in the city. Even it's doors are beyond
imagination. Inside of the temple entrance, the walls are made of gold and
adamantite.

name: A Small Gnome House
description:
This is a small suburban house made from quality wood.  You can see the
expert workmanship that went into making it, but it lacks creativity.

name: Dank, dark, smelly hole.
description:
This hole must have been used as a lair or nest.  There are
feathers and bones everywhere and the floor is covered with
something disgusting.

name: A Mountain Path
description:
You are on a mountain path which ascends a steep mountainside.  The trail
curves around the mountain so that you cannot really see what lies ahead.
You do sense great power though coming from the area behind the mountain.

name: Northern Lake Side.
description:
Floating on this boiling lake is not what you would consider an enjoyable
experience.  Many a creature bumps the bottom of your boat, and glares
at you through unblinking eyes from the waters below.  The southern
portion of the lake looks calm and serene compared to this wild place.

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: Fungus patch
description:
As you walk through the fungus patch, you are shot at by many millions of
spores. You can hardly breathe.

name: The Tomb of Cristis
description: Everything here has simply been destroyed.   Exits lead north and west.

name: The End of the Rainbow Bridge
description:
You have reached the end of the Rainbow Bridge.  Asgard stretches out above
you.  Looking around, you search for the legendary guardian of Asgard.  The
clouds are far below you and a sense of beauty and peacefulness surrounds you.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above poor alley.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: A small path in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The forest seems to
become lighter to the west.  The path continues north and west.

name: Humid, damp tunnel
description:
As the tunnel leads south it gets more humid and damp.  Moss covers the
walls and ferns even grow in the cracks here and there.  To the north it
seems much more sterile.

name: The Slave Pit
description:
You have entered the slave pit.  A voice blares in the distance,
"Get back to work, maggots!"  Rails upon rails of mined gold and silver
clutter the trail beneath you.

name: Door to Castle
description:
Here there is a door to the castle to the east.  The castle
is elegantly designed, and looks much like a roll of toilet paper
standing on end.  A sign says:

******************************************
*  WELCOME TO THE CASTLE OF STRANGELOVE  *
*      Here, celibacy is uninvited       *
******************************************

name: The greenhouse
description:
This is Dragons' greenhouse. Green light filters in slantwise through the
plants, giving the room a subtropical ambience. It is not really hot in here,
though, rather a pleasantly warm temperature. The walls are all windows, except
the eastern one joining the greenhouse to the main building, but it is hard to
see out for all the greenery here. There is a set of easy-chairs and a glass
coffee table. To the south, there is a wide double door out to a sunlit
terrace.

name: The Library
description:
You have entered a huge room, filled with books.  A peaceful man is
sitting at a table, studying.

name: Mage's Academy
description:
The mages academy is fairly well decorated see that the drow prefer magic
over physical power greatly.

name: A Small Clearing
description:
You are inside a small clearing.  You can see that there are signs of a
living creature nearby.

name: A Small Gnome House
description:
This is a small suburban house made from quality wood.  You can see the
expert workmanship that went into making it, but it lacks creativity.

name: Southern Lake Side.
description:
You are floating on a calm section of blue crystal water.  You feel much more
at ease then you were before in this area.  Then a wave of fear passes over
you.  You are not alone.

name: A Mountain Path
description:
You are on a rocky mountain path leading up and around a steep mountainside.
You sense a glow from the area beyond the mountain, which you cannot see yet.

name: Large, sturdy ledge.
description:
You are on a ledge above a steep cliff face.  You can climb down
if you want, but be careful!  After viewing the scenery, you notice
two small caves here, one north and one west.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: Fungus path
description:
As you walk along the path, millions of spores are shot at you. You can
hardly breathe.

name: An intersection in the light forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the forest.  A path leads north to a
small field and other paths lead east and west into the dense forest.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above the ground north of Midgaard.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads north and west.  An old tomb is here.

name: Administration room
description:
The elders gather here to discuss training strategies and count their
loot.  You notice papers which look like important secret documents
lying around. An escape passage leads west.

name: The Tether Path
description:
Another tether path just like the rest of them.  Surprisingly well
-lit by the golden orbs that hang from the sides, you can see the paths
become finer and finer in quality.

name: The dining hall
description:
This is Dragons' dining hall. There is a large long solid oak table,
seating at least 24, with heavy, wooden chairs to match. The oak panel walls
are filled with paintings. There are doors to the north and east, and to the
west there is a wide double door opening out onto the sunlit terrace.

name: Inside the entrance
description:
Everything here is covered in soot and very grimy.  The path continues
to the east and north, and there is a door to the west.

name: The Sanctum
description:
This small room is modestly decorated with small dragon icons.  Its sole
occupant is deep in thought.

name: City street
description:
You walk along a highly ornate city street going eastward. To the north is
a building.

name: A Small Gnome House
description:
This is a small suburban house made from quality wood.  You can see the
expert workmanship that went into making it, but it lacks creativity.

name: Beach
description:
You are on a sandy shore.  Marsh life creeps across the surface.  To the west
lies an evil fortress.  You see figures walking along the battlements.

name: An Edge of the Galaxy
description:
You are on the very edge of the galaxy.  Nothing is here except that there
is a path which leads down.

name: Fungus temple
description:
You find yourself standing inside of a giant mushroom. The inside
is decorated in the fashion of a temple.

name: Mountainside Tombs
description:
There are a few stone heaps here and there, the tombs of those who did not
last the arduous journey up the mountain.  Curiously you notice a few
uncovered bodies which don't seem to have died of exhaustion.  The path curves
east around the mountain.

name: Entrance Chamber to the Grand Hall of Kings
description:
Whoever built this place must have been very rich indeed!  Though you did
enter through a rather small door this place has enough room to hold several
score of people.  The floor has a beautifully woven carpet, and the walls are
covered in finely crafted tapestries. You can tell that these things must have
been worth much but they have not lasted well throughout the ages.  Massive
doors lead off to the south and a large stone staircase leads up.

name: Absolutely disgusting lair.
description:
The stench in here is quite foul.  There are feathers, bones and
rotting carcasses everywhere.  This place is absolutely gross and
you have to strain yourself not to lose your lunch.

name: A small path in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The forest seems to
become lighter to the east.  The path continues north and east.

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above bakery and cleric guild.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: N/S hallway
description:
The hallway continues to become more important-looking as you wander
south.  A room to the east looks rather more pleasant that some of the
others.

name: A Road Crossing
description: Another shifty little strand of webs, almost ethereal in nature.

name: The terrace
description:
You are standing on a sunlit terrace in front of Dragon's mansion. To the
west, there is a splendid view over the field down over the lake. To the north
is the greenhouse, its large windowpanes shimmering with weird and wonderful
colors, while a double door leads into the house proper to the east. It is
warm and calm here. There is a white-painted table with a parasol here,
together with a matched set of chairs.

name: Path
description:
You are on a path in the dwarven village which leads north to the shops
and south to the corner of the area.

name: Slave Chamber
description:
The room is in shambles. Straw is strewn all about the room as beds for the
unfortunate creatures who have fallen prey to drow imperialism.

name: The Court Ends
description:
You have reached the end of the court.  A huge Draconian is sitting in a
chair here.  As you enter, he motions with his hand and you are rushed by three
of his bodyguards.

name: Very Near to a Gigantic Star
description:
You are very near to a gigantic red star.  While you are still fascinated
by its beauty, the star keeps on growing ... suddenly you realize that you'd
better leave.

name: A Small Gnome House
description:
This is a small suburban house made from quality wood.  You can see the
expert workmanship that went into making it, but it lacks creativity.

name: Before the Great Gates.
description:
You stand before the gates of a huge fortress.  The drawbridge is up, the
gates closed, and the portcullis down.  This place looks very dangerous,
and you decide not to continue onward.

name: Absolutely disgusting lair.
description:
The stench in here is quite foul.  There are feathers, bones and
rotting carcasses everywhere.  This place is absolutely gross and
you have to strain yourself not to lose your lunch.

name: The Grand Hall of Kings
description:
A long hallway stretches east and west.  On the southern side of the hall
there are many doors, each with the name of a king who has died and is
entombed here.  The hallway is beautiful yet chilling.  Even though the area
has been kept well by acolytes, there remains a stench of the undead.

name: A small path in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  The crowns of the
old trees leave the forest in an unreal twilight illumination.  The path
continues south and west.

name: Sloping passage
description: You follow a path sloping down from the fungus temple.

name: A Blind Curve on the Mountain Path.
description:
This looks like a normal mountain path, but it is NOT!  This section of the
path is habitated by a huge (and of course, man-eating) Cyclops.  The path
makes its final ascent to an overlook.

name: Mid-level leader's room
description:
A rather nice looking room considering the drab conditions down here.
Through all the signs of decoration you can still see evidence of water
leaks.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads north and south.  An old tomb is here.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above main street.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: A Leader Strand
description:
This strand is weightier, more sturdy.  It shimmers as you step on
it.  You are definitely not in the Midgaardian realms anymore.  Just
where you are you can't tell.  It feels like you're moving through
ether.  You can still get back down to more surer lands.

name: Turn in road
description:
You are on a path that leads to a Hide & Tooth shop to the west, and the
path continues to the south.

name: At the edge of the grove
description:
You are standing at the entrace of a beautiful grove of trees, and your
heart is filled with pure, peaceful thoughts.  This looks like a safe place
to recover from the wounds of adventuring.  A faint path through the grove
lies to the north, and you can see the eastern road to the south.

name: bedroom
description: This is the personal room of the draconian king.  It is not empty.

name: A Gnome Shop
description:
You are in one of the several shops of this fine town.  The wares look fine,
but unfortunately the gnomes don't do business with outsiders.

name: Too Bright to Tell
description:
Indeed it is too bright to tell.  Because what you are witnessing is the
rare event of a Supernova, how a star explodes itself into galactic dust.
You may find yourself lucky to witness this rare event but even luckier,
you have finally got out of this galaxy as your body turns into dust.
That really HURTS!

name: City street
description:
You walk along a highly ornate city street leading west and south. To the
north is a relatively small house.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: A small path in the dense forest
description:
You are on a small path leading through the dense forest.  To the west there is
a cave entrance.  The path continues north and east.

name: The Shrine of Crotus
description:
Mostly rubble, this place used to be the shrine of the famous king Crotus,
