who saved the northern regions from being overrun by the goblin hordes of
100 years ago.  If not for him, Midgaard of course would have eventually been
conquered as well.  Though Crotus was a goodly king, it was rumored that he
turned to the dark ways in his dying years ... and died an evil man.

name: Vista
description:
This is a stunning vista overlooking a canyon.  There is a sign here that says:

BEHOLD -- ELEMENTAL CANYON

Fire leaps up from firepits in the western part of the canyon.  The sky looks
funny, and the air seems hazy to the northwest.  Electricity sparks
intermittently in the northeast.  To the east you see a strong, magic-looking
river flowing through the canyon.  Also to the east you spy a cave entrance
leading into the canyon wall.  The path descends to the north to another
overlook.

name: Sloping passage
description: You are on a path that gently slopes up from the underground pool.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 40 meters above the armoury.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Mess hall
description:
The a huge table with an immaculate white table cloth stretches way off
to the south.  The room is kept immaculately clean by the nights
themselves.  They truly belive that cleanliness is next to godliness.

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: Road to Newfane
description:
You are on a gently curving north-south road.  On your east side a youthful
river sparkles blue and rushes in the sunlight.  On the west, green leaves and
green ferns burst against the rich brown earth.  You feel the heat of your
healthy muscles as you travel swiftly down the well-paved road.
You may recall now if you like.

name: The Entrance of the Ethereal Web
description:
You are at the entrance to ethereal web.  Flickering in and out,
in and out, each strand reveals a different hue from black to green
to blue.

name: Inside the grove
description:
As you walk among the stately oaks of this grove, you feel at peace and
in harmony with this beautiful forest.  If only the rest of the lands were
so tranquil.  The trail turns towards the east, leading into the secluded
trees of the druids' holy grove, and a path back to the eastern road lies
south.

name: Hide & Tooth Shop
description:
You are in the Hide & Tooth shop.  Here you may buy the finest in Dwarven
weapons and armors. The path continues to the north and east.

name: Entrance to the Crypt
description:
You have entered a large room which smells heavily of reptile.  You wonder
what awaits you here.

name: A Gnome Shop
description:
You are in one of the several shops of this fine town.  The wares look fine,
but unfortunately the gnomes don't do business with outsiders.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: The Star Cluster
description:
You are inside the home of the stars.  All you can see around you are stars
and nothing else.  You eyes become pretty hurt as you look at them.

name: 4th house
description:
You stand inside the 4th house of the city. Its inner courtyard is rather
dull by drow standards and rather small as well.

name: Inside the cave
description:
You are in a natural cave.  Various sorts of debris cover the stone floor,
emitting a rather unpleasant smell that makes the air thick and hard to
breathe.  The only obvious exit is east.

name: The Tomb of Crotus
description:
A sarcophagus lies in the middle of the room and seems undisturbed.
A hole has been knocked into the east wall.

name: The Overlook
description:
You see various elemental servants wandering around the canyon.  The noise of
humming coming from the canyon gets louder.  The path makes a steep descent
into the canyon here.

name: The Sands of Sorrow
description:
A vast desert stretches for miles, the sand constantly shifting around you.
You feel lost.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above poor alley.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads east and south.  An old tomb is here.

name: N/S hallway
description:
The hallway continues north and south.  A peculiar kind of glow seems
to come from somewhere further along the hallway to the south. The room
to the east looks like the lap of luxury.

name: The Young Wormkin's Crib
description:
A playpen of sorts, with maggots of wasps and other baby vermin
lying about.  You feel that humans have been played with here too,
and eaten later.  You sense that the maker of this place has
an appetite for dragon meat, and uses this room as a breeding
area.

name: Newfane Village Square
description:
You are on the lawn of the village square of Newfane, resting against an oak
after your vigorous journey.  The late spring breeze feels warm and sensuous
on your body.  An Ale is in progress: you spy more than a dozen fiddlers and
hundreds of Morris Dancers dressed in white cotton and wearing colorful hats
and bells.

name: Path to the north of shop
description:
You are on a path to the north of the Hide & Tooth shop.  The path continues
to the north, and there is Granite Head's bakery to the west.

name: The fog
description:
You are in a grey fog, falling, screaming in pain as you realize
that you are being torn to nothing, atom by atom, falling and falling
and falling ...
...
.

name: Crypt
description:
You are in a large room which continues to the west.  You notice many
coffins here.  Open coffins reveal remains of something other than man.
The smell of reptile is very strong here.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: A Gnome Shop
description:
You are in one of the several shops of this fine town.  The wares look fine,
but unfortunately the gnomes don't do business with outsiders.

name: Another Edge of the Galaxy
description: This is another uninhabited place.  Exits lie north, east and south.

name: Throne Room
description:
The throne room is basically similar to the inner courtyard in regards
to decor. there is a small throne behind the altar but that is about it.

name: On a small, grassy field
description:
You are in a small, grassy field somewhere in the forest.  The tall grass
nearly reaches your waist, and the surrounding oaks and beeches form an almost
wall-like thicket on all sides of the field.  A small path leads south through
the trees.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: Entrance to Elemental Canyon
description:
You are awed by the sounds and sights of great powers at works here.
Elemental servants bustle back and forth doing the biddings of the elemental
rulers.  You see a sort of cross roads to the north, and you can climb up to
the overlook here.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 30 meters above the temple spire.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: The Sands of Sorrow
description:
A vast desert stretches for miles, the sand constantly shifting around you.
You feel lost.

name: High officer's room
description:
First thing you notice in this room is the pleasant aroma of cedar.  All
the paneling in the room is made of fine cedar.  A painting of an
elegant knight hangs on the wall.

name: The Base of the Web
description:
Large strands connect at this point.  The node shimmers and
flickers within the ether.  You see many flying creatures--
insects, pegasi, and dragon wormkins--navigate the dangerous
passages of the web.  Exits go in many directions.

name: A Large Dance Hall
description:
You are inside a large dance hall with a very polished, very slippery wooden
floor.  You see three long lines of dancers, alternating men and women, in
some sort of progressive country dance.  Two fiddlers, a flautist, and a
harpsichord player provide the music.  You hear scattered screams of joy
from the dancers.
You may recall now if you like.

name: North of Shops
description:
Here the path bends to the east towards the barracks. To the
south you can see the shops.

name: Path by a Stream
description:
You are on a small path leading north and west, that is surrounded on the
other two sides by a small stream.  The water looks mighty cold.

name: The Lair
description:
You have entered a large room dominated by a great white dragon.  It growls
at you before it attacks.

name: A fluffy white cloud.
description:
You find yourself standing on a small cloud.  The cloud feels kind
of spongy beneath your feet.  You find it hard to see anything in
the distance as wisps of cloud blow over your face.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: A narrow trail through the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a narrow trail winding its way between the enormous, grey trunks.
The crowns of the trees must be very dense, as they leave the forest floor in
utter darkness.  The trail leads east and west.

name: Entrance Way
description:
You stand in the entrance way to the temple which opens up to the north
into a large hallway going east and west. Small statues of spiders line the
entrance way's walls.

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at all.
In general, it is calm, yet there is always a incessant buzz of things
going on about.  The canyon continues north and east.

name: Corner of the Galaxy
description:
You wonder why the galaxy is limited.  All you have done in Astronomy
courses now prove worthless.  Well who told you to take one at the start?

name: The Sands of Sorrow
description:
A vast desert stretches for miles, the sand constantly shifting around you.
You feel lost.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads north and west.  An old tomb is here.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above the temple square.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: Mossy intersection
description:
There is a turn off to the passage here.  The main passage leads north
and south. To the south it seems to get impossibly darker.  To the east
you hear... birds?  A small rivulet of water seeps in from the passage
east.  The air is very humid and damp here.

name: Through the Trees
description:
This part of the web intersects through the branches of some
trees.  Various leaves and other debris that the many drones
have not picked up yet lie here.

name: A Small Hall
description:
You are inside a small hall with a rough wooden floor.  You see dozens of
people in the hall chasing one poor man who is yelling at the top of
his lungs.  Wait a minute.  These people are all holding hands and smiling!
The man in front is leading them in a spiral!  They're DANCING!  And you
thought people didn't dance like this any more!
You may recall now if you like.

name: Path by Hospital
description:
Here the path passes by the Hospital to the north.  It continues
to the east to the barracks, and to the west.

name: A Lair
description:
You have entered a large room dominated by a great black dragon.  It looks
as though it is amused by your presence.

name: Path by a Stream
description:
You are on a small east-west path.  The path shows new grass, as if it
has stopped being used sometime in the recent past.  A river is to the south,
and a small hut is to the west.

name: Sleepy little cloud.
description:
This cloud is peacefully snoozing away, enjoying himself.  There
is grumpy cloud to the east and a rather shy cloud north of here.

name: A narrow trail through the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a dusty trail winding its way east-west between huge, ancient trees
whose grey trunks remind you of ancient pillars in a enormous, deserted hall.
To the south, a frail path leads away from the trail.

name: The Grand Hall of Kings
description:
You are in the western part of the Grand Hall of Kings.  To the south is a
door and to the east and west the hall continues.

name: Elemental Gateway
description:
To the west a path dips and winds among some flowing firepits.  To the
northeast a path goes toward the river.  Beyond toward the northeast and
northwest are outcrops which rise up from the canyon floor. To the east there
is a cave mouth which leads into the canyon wall.  And to the south the path
leads up, away, and out of the canyon.  Various pure and cross-breeds of
elemental forms wander the canyon floor, which extends in a wide swath
northwards.

name: Hallway
description:
You are in a long hallway lined with adamantite. The walls are engraved
with pictures of elves and spiders. The hallway continues east and west. As you
look down the hallway you can make out one or two figures moving away from you.
To the north is a obsidian stairway.

name: Lost in Space
description:
You are now lost in space.  Compasses don't work here, sorry.  What's more
you can sense darkness engulfing you.  You'd better get out quick.

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above market square.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The Sands of Sorrow
description:
A vast desert stretches for miles, the sand constantly shifting around you.
You feel lost.

name: The holy grove
description:
A small grove of birches grow seem to grow from solid rock.  You hear
birds singing but try as you might you cant see any.  A strange glow
emanates from a place somewhere to the southeast in the grove.

name: Above the Clouds
description:
You can see all of Midgaard in this ethereal web.  Many
of the larger dragons that do wish to fly seem to fly
away from the sticky strands of the web.

name: Path next to barracks
description: Here the path continues west, and east to the barracks.

name: Road by a Pond
description:
You are passing by a large pond, almost a small lake.  You notice a small
wooden shack by the side of the road.
You may recall now if you like.

name: Grumpy little cloud.
description:
This cloud mutters and grumbles at you.  You have to jump quickly
to avoid a lightning bolt that passes by your toe.  Your aren't
sure but you think you hear the cloud snicker.

name: The Crypt Ends
description:
You have come to the end of the Crypt.  It seems deserted.  There is a
strange coffin lying against the wall.

name: A narrow trail through the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a dusty trail winding its way east-west between huge, ancient trees
that stand close on all sides.  Not a sound is to be heard - everything is
ominously quiet.

name: A Small Hut
description:
The hut is a mess!  Blood has stained the grass walls into a dark rich
crimson color.  Torn clothes and trash lie all around, and you think you
see a skeleton in the corner.

name: The Bottom of the Rainbow
description:
You are standing before a shimmering rainbow arching high up into the
sky.  You feel somehow separated from the natural world, even though the
temple spire is only a few meters below you.

name: A Dark Alleyway
description:
The walls of the alleyway have been spray-painted over many times
over the years.  One section of graffiti actually looks legible,
it says:    This section has been designed for levels 5 through 10
If you are above level 15 please don't expect much fun.
If you are below level 5 enter at your own risk.
Another section of graffiti says "Raff Rules!"
There is a boulevard to the east and Emerald Avenue is visible to the west.

name: The Shrine of Mitnar
description:
Mitnar was a gruesome beast of a man ... he loved battle ... and nothing
else.  Warriors did love Mitnar, and all fighting men honored him.
On the wall is depicted battle after battle after battle.
A small opening has been shaped carefully to the east.

name: Black Hole
description:
Well you have chosen the wrong path, sorry.  Nothing can escape from this
monster, not even light.
PANIC!  You can't escape!

name: Long Hallway
description:
You are in a long hallway lined with adamantite. The walls are engraved
with pictures of elves and spiders. The hallway continues east and west. As you
look down the hallway you can make out one or two figures moving away from you.

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at
all.  In general, it is calm, yet there is always a incessant buzz of
things going on about.  The canyon floor extends north and west.  There is a
cave mouth set into the canyon wall to the east.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads south and west.  An old tomb is here.

name: The Sands of Sorrow
description:
A vast desert stretches for miles, the sand constantly shifting around you.
You feel lost.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above market square and commons square.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: The holy grove
description:
The trees seem real enough even though they take root in solid rock.
You hear other small animals scampering through the light undergrowth
yet you see nothing. The grove continues south, east and west. An out of
place passage way for some reason heads north.

name: On A Cloud
description:
Rather thick in consistency.  You realize this is not
a typical cloud, but it might be the nest of an aerial creature.

name: An Old Wooden Church
description:
As you enter the hall, you see the largest crowd of people you've ever seen in
your life.  They're also the noisiest crowd you've ever heard, and as they
press around you, the SWEATIEST crowd you've ever felt!  At the front of the
hall, a group of musicians are playing 'Chorus Jig'.

name: Happy little cloud.
description:
You hear the cloud humming a little song to itself, but you can't
figure out the song.

name: Entrance to the Great Hall
description:
You have entered a huge hall.  It has been carefully decorated with
beautiful tapestries depicting a great battle between dragons and men.  The
dragons appear to be the victors.

name: Entrance to barracks
description:
Here there is an entrance to the barracks to the south, and
the path continues to the west.

name: On the Stream
description:
The stream is cold and frigid, yet it supports plenty of life beneath its
surface.  The current trickles west and there is a field to the south.

name: A narrow trail through the deep, dark forest
description:
You are where the dusty trail bends, as to avoid conflict with a colossal
trunk to the west.  Not a sound is to be heard - everything is ominously quiet.
The trail leads east and south.

name: The Tomb of Mitnar
description:
The wall paintings show men and women warriors alike bowing down to Mitnar,
prisoners of war being put to the sword by Mitnar, and great heaps of gold
and weapons under the feet of Mitnar.  Where his coffin was, there is now
only a rectangular blemish on the floor of the dusty room.

name: On the Rainbow
description:
You are standing on the rainbow, surrounded by many beams of multicoloured
light.  Through the bottom of the rainbow you can barely make out the Temple
of Midgaard, which is now quite far away.

name: The Homes of the Pleiades
description: This is where the famous Seven Sisters live.  You'd better not disturb them.

name: Beginning of White Dragon Boulevard
description:
This section of town has been overrun by the Troll gang.  Even the
police stay out of here for fear of being brutalized.  This was once
a nice lower-middleclass neighborhood, but know the gangs run the
streets.  All the shops and homes have been boarded up and abandoned.
An alleyway is to the west and the street continues east.  An over-
grown lot is to the south.

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: Long Hallway
description:
You are in a long hallway lined with adamantite. The walls are engraved
with pictures of elves and spiders. The hallway continues east and west. As you
look down the hallway you can make out one or two figures moving away from you.
To the north is a door.

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at
all.  In general, it is calm, yet there is always an incessant buzz of
things going on about.  The canyon floor extends off to the north, east,
and south.

name: In the air ...
description:
You are flying!
Currently you are about 60 meters above commoners square and the dump.
It seems like you can see forever!

name: A Link in the Ethereal Web
description:
This is another link in the ethereal web.  Various creatures
seem to get caught (or hypnotized) by its sticky strands.

name: The Sands of Sorrow
description:
A vast desert stretches for miles, the sand constantly shifting around you.
You feel lost.

name: The holy grove
description:
The grove continues west and south.  The glow is roughly to the south
somewhere.

name: Mountain Road
description:
You are following a road at the top of a mountain ridge with sky all around
you.  Distant valleys are spread out below you on both sides.  There are
many horsemen and horsewomen on this road, riding hell-for-leather out of
sheer exhilaration.  You wish you had a horse!
You may recall now if you like.

name: The Great Hall
description:
You are working your way down the Hall.  To the north, you notice a smaller
passageway, while the main hall continues to the east.

name: A small path in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a narrow path leading through the deep, dark forest.  You feel as if
the ancient trees observe you in watchful silence.  The path continues north
and south.

name: Bashful little cloud.
description:
This cloud blushes and tries to avoid your glance as you look at
your surroundings.  You decide that overall it is a peaceful little
cloud.

name: On the Stream
description:
The current here flows from the east, but a logjam blocks you from
continuing onward.

name: Guard House
description:
You are in the guard house to the west of the entrance
to the castle.  There are nude posters covering the walls.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: On the Rainbow
description:
You are standing on the rainbow, surrounded by many beams of multicoloured
light.  Through the bottom of the rainbow you see the City of Midgaard and the
land surrounding it.  It seems to be miles below you.

name: Western Side of the Temple
description:
You are still wandering around this temple.  You notice exits lie in all
directions except west.

name: Along White Dragon Boulevard
description:
Everywhere you look you see signs of recent violence.  Patches of blood
lie everywhere and broken sticks and abandoned knifes are strewn here
and there.  An over-grown lot is to the south.  White Dragon Boulevard leads
east and west.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads north and east.  An old tomb is here.

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at
all.  In general, it is calm, yet there is always an incessant buzz of
things going on about.  The canyon floor extends in all directions.

name: Long Hallway
description:
You are in a long hallway lined with adamantite. The walls are engraved
with pictures of elves and spiders. The hallway continues east and west. As you
look down the hallway you can make out one or two figures moving away from you.

name: Yule Tree Farm
description:
This is the Yule Tree Farm at the top of Mountain Road.  All around you,
young Yule Trees saturate your senses with dark green needles and pine
essence.

name: Mess hall
description:
"mess" isn't exactly the best word to describe this room.  On the
contrary, it is immaculately clean.  A very long table stretches way off
to the north. A hallway is to the east.

name: The Tenuous Strand
description:
Very windy here since it goes up into the sky somewhat.
Still, it's safe enough to move around.

name: The Sands of Sorrow
description:
A vast desert stretches for miles, the sand constantly shifting around you.
You feel lost.

name: Entrance to Mega-City One
description:
A road begins here in the glowing sands.  You follow it through a gate
in a Plasteen wall onto the Megway of Mega-City One.

name: First Barrack room
description:
Here is the first of two main rooms of barracks.  The
barracks continue to the south, and you can leave the room
to the north.

name: A Narrow Passageway
description: This Passageway branches off from the main hall and leads somewhere ... where?

name: The Field of Mice's Dreams
description:
This is a large green field of waist high grass.  You feel something
scurry over your feet.  There is a cave to the east.

name: On the Rainbow
description:
You are standing on the rainbow, surrounded by many beams of multicoloured
light.  The rainbow extends above and below you as far as you can see.

name: A small path in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a narrow path leading through the deep, dark forest.  Ancient grey
trees loom all around you.  The path continues north and west.

name: Sneezing little cloud.
description:
The cloud is wracked with sneezes.  At first you thought you were
in an earthquake before you realize where you are!

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: Orion's Hunting Lodge
description:
This is dedicated to the Great Hunter of all time -- Orion.
Scattered on the floor is the famous hunting equipment used by him.

name: White Dragon Boulevard at Armory
description:
Only gang members dare wander the streets here.
What used to be the armory lies to the south.  White Dragon Boulevard
leads east and west.

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at
all.  In general, it is calm, yet there is always an incessant buzz of
things going on about.  The canyon floor extends north, south, and west.
A path follows a stream to the east.

name: Long Hallway
description:
You are in a long hallway lined with adamantite. The walls are engraved
with pictures of elves and spiders. The hallway continues east and west. As you
look down the hallway you can make out one or two figures moving away from you.

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: The Void
description:
You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.

name: The dark woods
description:
You are travelling through woods that are as dark as night. The trees above
block all light and wind. The air is stagnant and smells of death and decay.
The lack of sounds and other signs of life make your skin crawl and you feel
very much like turning back and heading for safer areas. The path leads north
into more open lands while it also leads south into the darkness of the forest.
A small sign is posted here.

name: End of a hallway
description:
You hear voices coming from a room to the west.  the hallway goes north.
To the east lies a room which seems to glow with power and piety.

name: The Elder Wormkin's Room
description:
A more mature wormkin it seems resides here.  Various tomes of
arcane lore clutter the area, along with shards of armor and weaponry.

name: The Sands of Sorrow
description:
A vast desert stretches for miles, the sand constantly shifting around you.
You feel lost.

name: Mahmount Allesh Megway
description:
You are on one mile of over 13 and a half billion kilometers of
roadway in Mega-City One.  The Megway continues north and south.

name: Lair
description:
You have entered a large lair with bones strewn about the ground.  You
notice the source of these as you come face to face with a rather large red
dragon.  You notice a trap door in the floor.

name: The Dark Cave
description:
The cave gleams as your light reflects off of it.  As you squint your eyes
and try to look ahead, you think you see something move.

name: Back of Barracks
description:
Here is the back of the dwarven barracks.  There are rows
of beds here, and there is a stench that is unbearable.

name: On the Rainbow
description:
You are nearing the end of the rainbow.  The beams of multicoloured
light have begun to merge and solidify.  All around you you see glowing
starlike motes of dust.  Ahead of you is a bridge.

name: Dopey little cloud.
description:
This cloud is too busy daydreaming to watch where its going.  It
doesn't even notice you landing on it.  It looks like it couldn't
figure its way out of an open box.

name: A junction in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are by a junction where three paths meet.  Ancient grey trees tower above
you on all sides.  Paths lead east, south and west.

name: White Dragon Blvd.
description:
Black Dragon Avenue used to run south from here but the way has been
blocked by the toppling of a building into the street.  White Dragon
boulevard continues east and west.

name: Northern Side of the Temple
description:
You are still wandering around this temple.  You notice exits lie in all
directions except north.

name: The Grand Hall of Kings
description: You are still walking through the gloomy hallway.

name: A Gravel Path on the Graveyard
description:
You are on a gravel path winding its way between dark evergreen trees on
the graveyard.  The path leads south and west.  An old tomb is here.

name: Long Hallway
description:
You are in a long hallway lined with adamantite. The walls are engraved
with pictures of elves and spiders. The hallway continues east and west. As you
look down the hallway you can make out one or two figures moving away from you.
To the south is a door.

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at
all.  In general, it is calm, yet there is always an incessant buzz of
things going on about. The canyon floor extends north, east, and south.
To the west a garden is on fire.

name: Darker Cave
description:
The cave gets even darker as your terror grows stronger.  You fear for your
life as something emerges out of the shadows.

name: Underground Tunnel
description:
You have entered an underground tunnel.  It is dark and dirty, and you find
yourself wishing you were back in Midgaard.

name: The dark woods
description:
You wearily travel through the darkness of the forest. Huge skeletal trees
line the edges of the path and tower above you. Errant rays of light spear
down through the gaps in the canopy above and provide small spots of light
that seem to attract what little foliage can grow on the dark forest floor.
The path winds north and south into darkness.

name: Another Tree Limb
description:
Once again the web crosses another tree limb.  To the side you
see the possible entrance to another creatures lair.

name: The Sands of Sorrow
description:
A vast desert stretches for miles, the sand constantly shifting around you.
You feel lost.

name: Grand Templar's room
description:
All the items in this room look ancient yet strangely very powerful and
rich.  There is an aura of great holiness about the room.

name: Intersection of Junket Way and Megway
description:
The Megway intersects with Junket Way here.  Junket Way is to the east,
the Megway continues north and south, and the Pustule Palace Cafe is
to the west.

name: The Glowing Bridge at the Rainbow's End
description:
After a long climb you have reached the end of the rainbow.  The brilliant
colours have twisted and merged into a beautiful glowing bridge that leads
toward a massive white gate to the north.  All around you is a soft, peaceful
glow interrupted only by the passing of starlike dust motes before your eyes.

name: Inside of Castle Strangelove
description:
You are just inside the castle.  It is very tubular in shape,
and it is very featureless.  There is a set of stairs that lead
up, and the door leads out of the castle to the west.

name: A small path in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a narrow path leading through the deep, dark forest.  Ancient grey
trees loom all around you.  The path continues north and east.

name: Doc-like little cloud.
description:
The cloud looks at you through its Lennon like specs and examines
you quite scientifically.

name: Corner of Ice and White Dragon
description:
Ice Dragon Way leads south from here.  It used to run the whole length
of the neighborhood and way lined with beautiful crystal sculptures.
White Dragon boulevard leads east and west from here.

name: The Offering Chamber
description:
This is the sacred offering chamber in which sacrifices are made.  You see a
young girl here, chained to the wall, as if she is waiting for execution.
You look up and realize the chains are sent down directly from above.
Below you recognize the temple of Thalos.

name: The Shrine of Frath
description:
Little chunks of dried meat are spattered throughout this room.  The walls
are covered in gore.  Almost as if they were painted ... ICK!  You can
almost make out the design!

name: In a dusty Tomb
description:
You are in a dark burial chamber beneath a large tomb stone.
The only exit appears to be up.

name: Underground Tunnel
description: This tunnel has come to a dead end.  You feel nervous about being trapped here.

name: Warrior's Barracks
description:
The room is a complete mess. None of the beds are made, clothes and other
items have been left all about the room. Well drow warriors never were known
for neatness.

name: A Dusty Path
description:
You are on a well traveled path that leads in many directions.  To the north
is a large house, and to the west is a fortress.

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at
all.  In general, it is calm, yet there is always an incessant buzz of
things going on about.  The canyon floor extends in all directions.

name: A nomad camp
description:
This small group of desert nomads has stopped for the day to rest
and refresh themselves beside this beautiful oasis. Three tents and some
camels make up the party. From within two of the tents you hear muffled
voices, obviously surprised at your visit.

name: The Bird Spider's Lair
description:
This is a big game hunter among most spiders.  Crush jewels
and other weapons suggest the inhabitant must have powerful jaws.
Beware!

name: The small intersection in the forest
description:
The forest path splits here in three directions. Small paths lead to the east,
north, and south. The trees above leave a gap which allows light to fill the
intersection. It is almost as though you are in a circle of light that
provides sanctuary in this land of darkness.
Something has been scrawled in the dirt in blood here.

name: Mahmount Allesh Megway
description:
The traffic here is really congested due in part to the over 11 million
people driving Mo-Pads, the mobile homes which are constantly on the
move until their owners can find an apartment in one of the City-blocks.
The Megway continues north and south.

name: Very dark passage
description:
This room is so dark that even powerful magic lights seems to barely
illuminate the ground in front of you.  If its possible it seems even
darker to the south.  The passage also leads back north.

name: The Astral Gate
description:
Here the bridge ends before a massive, pearly-coloured gate beyond which
you can see a field of blackness filled with silvery snake-like tendrils,
stars, and occasional flashes of of light.

name: A narrow trail through the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a dusty trail winding its way between huge, ancient trees
standing close on all sides.  The trail leads north and west and to the south,
a frail path leads away from the trail.

name: White Dragon Boulevard
description:
A once majestic inn with a white marble facade lies to the south.
Unfortunately, it has fallen into disrepair and decay.  You can continue
east or west.

name: A store room
description:
There is a layer of dust on the floor at least 3 inches thick!  It is
probable that not many people have been in here for many months.

name: The Entrance of the Ancient Temple
description:
You have entered into this old temple, which was built originally for the gods
in Mount Olympia, but it is now deserted as someone took over this part of the
Universe.

name: Snowy, white cloud.
description:
You shiver as you stand here.  This beautiful, fluffy, pure white
cloud is snowing.  The snow is pure and sweet as it melts in your
mouth.  What a nifty cloud to be on.

name: The Tomb of Frath
description:
UGH!  The sarcophagus is opened up and the mummified body lies out in the
open, ripped to pieces.  Gnawed pieces of flesh and bone are strewn here.

name: Long Hallway
description:
You are in a long hallway lined with adamantite. The walls are engraved
with pictures of elves and spiders. The hallway continues east and west. As you
look down the hallway you can make out one or two figures moving away from you.

name: The Great Hall Ends.
description:
You have come to the end of the great hall.  You see before you a huge
golden door, it must be at least twenty feet tall!  It has beautiful etchings
of dragons.  You see a sign on the door.

name: The Iron Gateway
description:
You stand at the entrance to the gnome fortress.  The place seems to be
well fortified.

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at
all.  In general, it is calm, yet there is always an incessant buzz of
things going on about.  The Canyon floor extends north, south and west.

name: Inside a small tent
description:
This is a small and simple tent with few possessions in sight. Lying
here and there are young-looking men and women, possibly slaves to the
leader of this band.

name: A Link in the Ethereal Web
description:
This is another link in the ethereal web.  Various creatures
seem to get caught (or hypnotized) by its sticky strands.

name: The edge of the forest and hills
description:
You stand at the edge of a dark forest. A path leads north into the forest and
its deadly darkness and silence. Looking west, you see a path that leads up
into a foothills region. Standing here on the boundary between light and
darkness, you feel very vulnerable and alone.

name: Mahmount Allesh Megway
description:
The Megway continues north and south.  On the off-ramps here you see
many of the citizens of Mega-City One doing nothing.  You see of
every hundred citizens, it can be guaranteed that 87 of them will
be totally unemployed, and that a further five will not work more
than ten hours a week.  To the east there is a dark alley and to the
west is Rietzik's Shuggy Hall.

name: The holy grove
description:
The grove continues north and east.  To the east a strange humming can
barely be heard.

name: Into the Astral Plane
description:
You step through the gate, and into another reality...

You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is very disorienting, although it is not too late to return
through the gate to the south.

name: Wine cellar
description:
This room smells like wine, and you can only assume it used to be
a wine cellar at one time.

name: A narrow trail through the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a dusty trail winding its way east-west between huge, ancient trees
that stand close on all sides.  Not a sound is to be heard - everything is
ominously quiet.

name: Corner of Bronze and White Dragon
description:
This is the north-east corner of the neighborhood. White Dragon
boulevard heads west and Bronze Dragon street heads south.

name: Hercules' Mighty Throne
description:
You stand before the throne of a long-forgotten hero.  It is full of bounty
that he got from the Ten Labours.

name: Cold, damp cloud.
description:
Your mood grows grumpy as you find yourself cold and wet from this
dismal cloud.  You notice a rock outcropping above you.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: Grand Stairway
description:
You are standing at the bottom of a giant obsidian and adamantite
stairway. The edges are trimmed with gold.

name: THE Lair
description: You have entered a huge lair.  You feel that something big lives here or at least did.  The golden door lies back to the west.

name: A Long Hallway
description:
You are now inside of the fortress; you must be lucky that the guards
haven't killed you.  As you glance around, you notice that the walls and
floors are spotlessly cleaned.  The barracks are to the north and a
storage room is to the south.

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at
all.  In general, it is calm, yet there is always an incessant buzz of
things going on about. The canyon floor extends east and south.  You can
climb a rise in the canyon floor to the north.

name: Beside the camels
description:
Here stand about ten camels, all hitched to some stakes plugged into
the ground. To the east you see a small tent while to the north you see a
larger, fancier tent.

name: The Quiet Tree Top
description: Here is a quiet tree top.

name: Central Plaza
description:
You are at the Central Plaza of the downtown district.  There are a couple
of juves Boingging (tm) in the air above you.  Max Jaffa Boulevard goes
east, the Megway continues north and south, and Bazza's Home for the
Terminally Sarky is to the west.

name: In the dense forest
description:
You walk along a small path leading through a dark forest. No sounds can be
heard and little light penetrates the canopy of trees above you. The air here
smells musty and you long for a fresh breath. You see an intersection of paths
to the west. The path you are on leads south into the darkening woods.

name: The holy grove
description:
All of a sudden all the mysterious sounds of the grove stop. Or perhaps
its just the strange humming and glowing from a clearing to the south
drowning out everything else. There is a sort of magical forcefield door
to the south.

name: Exploring the Astral Plane
description:
You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is very disorienting, and it is difficult to maintain your
bearings and sense of direction.

name: Stairs in castle
description: The stairs continue to circle up and down here.

name: A narrow trail through the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a dusty trail winding its way between huge, ancient trees that stand
close on all sides.  The trail leads east and south.  To the north, a narrow
path leads away from the trail.

name: Eastern Side of the Temple
description:
You are still wandering around this temple.  You notice exits lie in all
directions except east.

name: Mysterious rock outcropping.
description:
This rock outcropping just seems to hang in midair.  To the north
you see a house and if you ease yourself down, you can land on a
rather damp, dismal cloud.  The door to the house is closed.

name: An over-grown lot
description:
A huge building was going to be built here, but they gave the
project up when violence took over the town.  Now it is just a
weed-strewn plot of land.  The lot continues east and there is a road north.

name: Grand Hallway
description:
You are standing in the middle of a grand hallway. The walls are
of the purest adamantite with gold trim. Mosaics line the walls.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: The End...
description:
You have reached the final lair.  It is dominated by a huge five headed
dragon.  You suddenly realize that you have SERIOUS problems...

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at
all.  In general, it is calm, yet there is always an incessant buzz of
things going on about.  The canyon floor extends east, south, and west.

name: On The Web
description:
RRRRRRRRRRROOOOOOOOOOOOOAAAAAAAAAAAAAARR!  You hear the roar
of a powerful beast.  Dragon, you think.  You shiver in your boots
as you tiptoe on this section of the web.

name: A Long Hallway
description:
You are now inside of the fortress; you must be lucky that the guards
haven't killed you.  As you glance around, you notice that the walls and
floors are spotlessly cleaned.  A mess hall is to the south.

name: The warrior's tent.
description:
This tent has a few furnishings, but mainly it holds the band's
protectors. They all stare at you coldly as you enter.

name: Corner of Ed Hilldreth Memorial Parkway and Megway
description:
Another major intersection which is being negotiated by vehicles that
are bound to minimum speed limits.  Many Slow Driving offenses are being
handed out by the Judges.  The Megway goes north and south, a Parkway
goes east, and Nu Phisog Parlour is west.

name: The dark forest path
description:
You continue on through darkness and gloom. The path below you has become a
wet quagmire. It is difficult to walk, and you make squishing sounds as you
move on. Looking east, you see a swampy path. The main path leads north and
south into darkness.

name: Stairs
description:
You are still circling around on the stairs.  You are starting to
get dizzy from going around and around and around and around and
around.  The stairs continue up and down.

name: Very dark caveway
description:
This room is so very dark that no one is quite sure whats in it, so
there's nothing really to describe except maybe the powerful sense of
evil coming from the east and the almost overcoming urge to run to the
west.

name: Exploring the Astral Plane
description:
You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is very disorienting, and it is difficult to maintain your
bearings and sense of direction.

name: Perseus' Chamber
description:
It is the chamber of the prince, Perseus.  However, he seems not to be here.
Maybe he has gone to get Pegasus to save Andromeda?

name: A narrow trail through the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a dusty trail winding its way north-south between huge, ancient
trees that loom ominously above you.

name: Foyer.
description:
Shadows play tricks on your eyes.  Everytime you think you see
something in a corner and turn to get a better look, nothing is
there.  The place is very dark.  Even with a torch, you have
trouble making out the room to the east.

name: East end of an over-grown plot of land
description:
This was planned to be a park, but the developer was scared out
of town by the gang.  Now it is just a dusty square of land. The
park was started to the south.  The lot continues west and there
is a street to the north.

name: The Grand Hall of Kings
description:
You are at the western end of the Grand Hall of Kings.  There is a
door leading north and the hallway continues west.

name: Mage's Barracks
description:
The mage's living quarters is rather clean with the exception of a few
used component containers. It is rather well decorated as well. Cots line the
floor for the mages to sleep on. the only door is to the west.

name: Stairwell
description:
This is an old decrepit stairwell that leads to the wine cellar.  It looks
like it hasn't been used for decades.  Well, at least not by anything living.

name: The Floor of the Canyon
description:
Various elemental forms wander the floor of the canyon.  Some seem to be
going about their business, while others seem to have no business at
all.  In general, it is calm, yet there is always an incessant buzz of
things going on about.  The canyon floor extends south and west.  You can
climb a rise in the canyon floor to the north.

name: The Barracks
description:
You now stand in the sleeping quarters of the gnome guards.  Every bed is
made perfectly, and not single article of clothing is on the floor.  There
is a small storage room to the east.

name: The Ki-Rin Chamber
description:
A wise ki-rin was entrapped here many years ago.  It is from her
that the ruler of this realm steals his magical strength.

name: Mahmount Allesh Megway
description:
As you travel the Megway you notice many citizens participating in their
favorite hobbies such as spot welding and metalwork, scratch building
fashion Kneepads, giving blood, or just looking out the window.  The
Megway continues north and south.

name: The main tent
description:
This tent is as lavishly decorated on the inside as it is on the
outside. A fancy carpet lies on the sand and numerous baskets line the
walls.

name: A turn in the path
description:
The forest path turns here towards the north and west. To the north, you see
that the ground has become dank and swampy, while the western path appears
to be entering a hilly area. You hear sounds of swamp creatures to the north
east.

name: Top of stairs
description:
You are at the top of the stairs in the castle.  There is an exit
to the east, and the stairs lead down.

name: Exploring the Astral Plane
description:
You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is very disorienting, and it is difficult to maintain your
bearings and sense of direction.

name: On the Mystic Chains
description:
You are dangling on the chains.  You notice exits lie in all directions.
Up above you see the chains continue upwards.  But a forcefield prevents
you from going further upwards.

name: Deep within the catacombs
description:
It stinks like a lair in here.  A rotten smell of humanoid flesh
lingers.  You stumble over what you think are corpses in the utter
darkness. You sense a evil growl from somewhere in the room. maybe
everywhere in the room. . ..

name: Armory
description:
Well actually, this is what USED to be the armory.  The equipment has
all been stolen or broken beyond repair. The back wall of the
building has been bashed down, allowing you to go south.  White
Dragon Boulevard is north.

name: Tower.
description:
You are in a musty old tower.  The smell of mold and mildew is
almost overpowering.  You hear strange creaks and groans ... is it
the wind or did someone (something?) make that noise.  To the west
is the house and there is a stairway leading up into the tower.

name: A narrow trail through the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a dusty trail winding its way between huge, ancient trees
standing close on all sides.  The trail leads north and west and to the east,
a frail path leads away from the trail.

name: The Shrine of Jubal
description:
This was once beautiful.  Now the huge tapestries have been torn down and the
carpeting pulled up ... the paintings on the ceiling are unreadable and the
altar is crumbled.

name: Grand Hallway
description:
You are walking down a grand hallway, heavily decorated with adamantite
and gold. To the north the hall goes down a flight of stairs while a door is
too the west.

name: Wine cellar
description:
This is the old wine cellar of the Dragon Tower.  The shelves are empty.
Nothing living has been in here for a long time.  You see a tunnel leading
off to the east and boy does it smell bad.  Kinda of like rotting flesh.

name: Dark Cave
description:
You notice a path winding east among some huge boulders.  You feel a powerful
source of energy from that direction.

name: A Small Storage Room
description:
This is where the gnomes store all their spare clothing and armor.
There is not much here, but you might come up with something.

name: A Link in the Ethereal Web
description:
This is another link in the ethereal web.  Various creatures
seem to get caught (or hypnotized) by its sticky strands.  To
the north you sense the heavy breathing of a fiery animal.

name: The main tent
description:
This is where the leader of this band of nomads resides. He is
definitely rich as you inspect the tapestries, baskets, and a few
paintings as well.

name: The bloody intersection
description:
This is a small intersection. Paths lead east, west, and south. You are struck
by the carnage here when you enter the clearing. There appears to have been a
great battle here. Blood is everywhere and the ground is all torn up. Pieces
of beaten armour and broken blades lie all around. Examining the tracks here
lead you to believe that the dead and wounded were dragged off in two
directions, south and east.

name: Mahmount Allesh Megway
description:
The Megway ends here.  To the west is Ziggi Piggi's Home for the
Semi-Stiff, to the east and south are construction areas, and the
Megway goes north.

name: Queen's waiting room
description:
This is the Queen's waiting room.  Here the men literally
'wait' for the queen.  You've heard that the queen really likes
to get to 'know' her people, in the biblical sense.  The queen's
bedroom is to the north, and you can see stairs to the west.

name: Witches Tower
description:
Here you see strange things of arcane value.  There is a cauldron in the
corner bubbling madly, belching a foul brew that must have come from hell.
On shelves lie jars of strange creatures you have never seen before, or
hope to again.  A picture of a familiar temple hangs on the east wall.

name: A Bend in the Way
description:
Ice Dragon Way bends east and south from here.  You notice a lot of
blood dried into the dirt here.

name: On a Hill
description:
Suddenly you find yourself on a hillside.  As you look around, you notice
that Spring has descended upon you.

name: Very dark cavern
description:
The cavern is hard to describe due to the extreme magical darkness.
Probing with a light source seems to reveal nothing but more darkness.

name: Exploring the Astral Plane
description:
You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is very disorienting, and it is difficult to maintain your
bearings and sense of direction.

name: Cleric's Barracks
description:
The bed chamber is brightly decorated with spider shaped statues, murals
and the like. Large beds line the floor making this a comfortable room to live
in.

name: The Tomb of Jubal
description:
The smell coming off of the opened sarcophagus is nauseating.  The floor is
slightly crumpled and walls are raked ... but the worst part is the mummy ...
Jubal the Benevolent is missing his head!

name: A small path in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a narrow path leading through the deep, dark forest.  Ancient grey
trees loom in all directions.  The path continues south and west.

name: Tunnel
description:
This tunnel seems to stretch for miles.  You try to distinguish the end but
your eyes soon tire from the strain.  The smell here has increased two fold.
The tunnel continues to go to the east.  The wine cellar lies back to the
west.

name: A Small Storage Room
description:
This is where the gnomes store all their spare weapons.  A door leads off
to the east.

name: Darker Caves
description:
You can barely see your way even with a light source.  The rocks of the cave
are even darker than the darkness.  You hear a powerful humming all around
you.  Cave paths go south and east roughly, its hard to tell exactly when you
can't see where you are going.

name: Yevaud's Lair
description:
Yevaud, the Usurper of Midgaard, resides here.  A voice cries
out, "BEWARE, the Usurper of Midgaard lives here!  FLEE while you can!"
But even Yevaud has his master...or so you deduce.

name: Strange Glowing Sand
description:
A vast desert stretches for miles, the sand constantly shifting around
you.  But this patch of desert looks different...the sand glows.  You see a
futuristic city to the south.

name: Junket Way
description: Junket Way a small Skedway continues east and west.

name: The rocky path
description:
The path here winds among the low rocky hills. The long trek up and down the
hills begins to tire you greatly. Looking east, you see a small clearing. More
hills are to the north of here.

name: Bedroom
description:
This is the Queen's bedroom.  The bed is all ruffled, and there
is a stack of dirty sheets piled in the corner.

A note has been scrawled in lipstick on the mirror:

I'm out looking for my birth control pills.
Why don't you slip into something comfortable while you're waiting?

name: Ice Dragon Bend
description:
Ice Dragon Way bends to the north and west here.  There are footprints
here.  They seem to indicate a large struggle took place here
recently.  What used to be the town Magic shop is to the east.

name: Suspicious little raincloud.
description:
On second glance, this cloud doesn't seem much like a raincloud.
A balloon sticks out of the top and you think you hear it humming
something like, 'Tut, tut!  It looks like rain!'

name: The holy place
description:
A glowing stone lies in the center of the clearing.  You recognize it as
the stone of the Excalibur.  The strange humming glowing makes it
difficult to see if the Excalibur is there or not. Might want to take a
closer look if possible.

name: Inside a Spanish Bull-Ring
description:
You are inside what used to be a ground for bull fighting.  But you notice
there are no Matadors around.  Maybe they are all dead?

name: Grand Stairway
description:
You are climbing a set of obsidian stairs surrounded by adamantite walls.
To the north are a set of large golden doors.

name: A junction in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are by a junction where three paths meet.  Ancient grey trees tower above
you on all sides.  Paths lead north, east and west.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: Exploring the Astral Plane
description:
You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is very disorienting, and it is difficult to maintain your
bearings and sense of direction.

name: A cave opening
description:
You stand at the opening of a giant cave.  There are many bones strewn across
the room.  Some human, some indistinguishable.  It smells very bad in here.
You can hear movement in the cave to the north.  The tunnel goes back to the
south.

name: A Small Storage Room
description:
This is yet another room for storing gnome stuff.  Maps and battle plans
are stored in neat stacks on the shelves.

name: The wind-swept ledge
description:
Being very careful not to lose your balance, you look around and
find that this canyon is about a half a kilometer deep. To the west is
a dark cave leading under the desert sands.

name: A Link in the Ethereal Web
description:
This is another link in the ethereal web.  Various creatures
seem to get caught (or hypnotized) by its sticky strands.  A single
spider line lies to the north, while ghastly seemings are due
southward.  The grim entrance of Arachnos' Lair is downward.

name: Darker Caves
description:
You can barely see your way even with a light source.  The rocks of the cave
are even darker than the darkness.  You hear a powerful humming all around
you.  Cave paths go south and west roughly; it's hard to tell exactly when you
can't see where you are going.

name: Davies Alley
description:
You are in a very dark and seedy alley.  This is just the right place for
a bite fight.  Bite fighting is an illegal activity where both combatants
can only use their sharpened teeth as weapons.

name: Hospital
description:
You are inside the Dwarven Hospital.  It smells like rubbing
alcohol, and there is blood all over the walls.

name: The rocky path
description:
The path here is very rocky and treacherous. The travelling is rough and you
slip and fall often. Looking south, you see that the path continues into the
hills. Smoother ground is to the east, but the path seems to lead into a dark
forest in that direction.

name: The remains of the magic shop
description:
The wizard was tough but he couldn't take on 50 of them at once.  So he
died and they took all his stuff and used it on their fellowmen.
The front door leads west back out to the street.  There is a back
door leading to another street to the east.

name: Misty passageway
description:
Warm mist swirl about you making you feel threatened as well as
protected at the same time.  The swirling mist makes it tough to tell
directions quite clearly, but you seem to be able to go north or south.
The mist gets denser to the south.

name: Inside a study
description:
This is a strange study. Besides the desks and chairs you also see a large
mirror in the middle.  So, you wonder, is this how you make a Gemini into
two Gemini?

name: Cirrus maximus cloud.
description: This cloud looks like it is of the cirrus maximus genre of clouds.

name: Main Chamber
description:
This is the south side of a large auditorium used for services by the
drow priestesses. In the center is a large sacrificial pit and beyond that is
an altar.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: Roaming the Astral Plane
description:
You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is somewhat disorienting.
All exits lead off into the astral field.

name: The End of the tunnel
description:
You have finally come to the end of the tunnel.  Back to the west lies
the miles of tunnels you have walked through.  You see the faint outline of
a trapdoor above you.  A bridge over an underground river lies to the south.

name: A small path in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a narrow path leading through the deep, dark forest.  You feel as
if the ancient trees observe you in watchful silence.  The path continues north
and west.

name: The Mess Hall
description:
You are in the room where the guards come to get their grub.  The benches
and tables are neatly cleaned and straightened, while shiny plates line
the walls.

name: The cave mouth
description:
The air in here is MUCH cooler than outside. From the west you hear
strange sounds, but can see nothing. The cave slopes down into the
darkness.

name: Entrance to the Donjonkeep
description:
A dark path at the end of the web strand, you see ahead
a torch lit chamber where the souls of unavenged adventurers
come and gnash their teeth.  The howls and screams of many echo
through the hall ways.  You see one definite path ahead.

name: Darker Caves
description:
You can barely see your way even with a light source.  The rocks of the cave
are even darker than the darkness.  You hear a powerful humming all around you.
Cave paths go north, south and east roughly; it's hard to tell exactly when
you can't see where you are going.

name: Max Jaffa Boulevard
description: Max Jaffa Boulevard continues east and west.

name: Up the rocky hillside
description:
You are climbing on a rocky hillside. As you scramble about, loose rocks and
small boulders bounce and fall down below you. Looking to the east and west,
you see more stable ground. The hillside itself goes on higher to the south
and it drops away to the north.

name: Granite Head's Bakery
description:
The aroma coming from this room is sensuous.  You can almost taste
the pastries dissolving in your mouth.

name: Along the seashore
description:
You start to feel the heat of Summer.  Amongst the rocky beach you notice
hidden forms which could be camouflaged crabs.

name: Eastern side of Chamber
description:
You are on the eastern side of the chamber overlooking the pit. To the east
is a door while to the north is an altar.

name: Bronze Dragon Street at wizard's back door
description:
Bronze Dragon street goes north and south.  The back door to what
remains of the magic shop is west.

name: Intersection of caverns
description:
Caverns head north, south and east from this peculiar spot. Medium
sized caverns from the east and the north join to form a huge cavern
heading south.  The walls of the cavern are made of a bizarre mixture
of many shiny crystals.

name: Raging hurricane.
description:
You are buffeted and knocked about by the almost godlike strength
of the raging hurricane.  It is hard to see and hear anything.
Your only thought is to seek refuge from the storm.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: The Bridge
description:
You are walking along an old wooden bridge.  Its not that secure.  You
might want to hurry along.  To the south, on the other side of the bridge,
lies a small opening.

name: Roaming the Astral Plane
description:
You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is somewhat disorienting.
All exits lead off into the astral field.

name: A Small Room
description: This is a small plain room.  Its only interesting feature is a ladder down.

name: A small path in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a narrow path leading through the deep, dark forest.  Giant, grey
trees loom ominously on all sides.  The path continues east and south.

name: The mysterious lair.
description:
You have stumbled upon the home of something. From the treasure
haphazardly strewn about and the rotting carcasses, you would guess that
this is a dragon's lair. As to what type, you can't really say. The cave
narrows out into a tunnel to the west.

name: Darker Caves
description:
You can barely see your way even with a light source.  The rocks of the cave
are even darker than the darkness.  You hear a powerful humming all around you.
Cave paths go north, south and west roughly, it's hard to tell exactly when you
can't see where you are going.

name: The Guardian's Room
description:
A chair sits here for a tireless guardian who ensures that no
soul escapes.  The room is undecorated.

name: Ed Hilldreth Memorial Parkway
description: The Parkway goes east and west.

name: The sparse foothills
description:
You are in foothills that are sparsely covered by scraggly bushes and weather
beaten trees. There are little signs of life here. Only bare rock and dry dirt
can be seen. Looking east, you see a small pass that will allow you to leave
the foothills. The foothills themselves extend to the south.

name: Dark path
description:
This path is very well worn, and there is an entrance to the mines to the
east, while the path continues to the north and west.

name: Dracolich Plaza
description:
They began construction of a pleasant plaza here, though you wouldn't
have known it if I hadn't told you.  It has been renamed in honor
of the Dragon gang's idol, the Dracolich.  It has become sort of a
training ground.  There is a short cut to the east and an overgrown
lot of land to the north.

name: Entrance to the burial grounds
description:
You have entered what appears to be a burial ground of sorts. The
templars buried their dead here.  Chills go down your spine as you feel
something watching you.  You hear the random groan of a ghost, the howl
of a wraith, and the dry clanking of bones.

name: Sacrificial Pit
description:
A you climb down into the pit thousands of spiders cover you tearing your
body to shreds.

Lloth thanks you for your sacrifice.

You've fallen, and you can't get up!!!

name: Within the Deep Jungle
description:
Nearby you can hear the roar of an animal.  Peering through the dense
overgrowth you think you glimpse a pair of menacing eyes.

name: Raging hurricane.
description:
You are buffeted and knocked about by the almost godlike strength
of the raging hurricane.  It is hard to see and hear anything.
Your only thought is to seek refuge from the storm.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: A small opening
description:
You are standing in a small opening.  To the north lies the old wooden
bridge.  To your south the you can see a clearing.  You can see sunlight
again.  What a welcome relief!

name: Roaming the Astral Plane
description:
You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is somewhat disorienting, though your instincts say you are
close to home.
All exits lead off into the astral field.

name: A Small Unused Room
description:
You stand in a small room in an unused section of the fortress.  The whole
room is coated with dust and cobwebs.  The ladder leads back up, and
a rusty door is to the east.

name: A junction in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are by a junction where three paths meet.  Ancient, grey trees seem to
observe you silently you from all sides.  Paths lead north, east and west.

name: Darkest Caves
description:
Your light doesn't even seem to work here.  Even magical light sources seem
only to illuminate about a foot ahead of you.  You suddenly realize that the
path has descended quite a bit but you didn't notice before because of the
darkness.  You sense a great presence off to the east aways.

name: A wide tunnel
description:
This tunnel seems to go on forever into the darkness. You carefully
feel your way along the walls.

name: Realm of the Hopeless
description:
Here you see many misguided souls who think they still live.
They search for those who killed them without warrant, and seek the
free souls of living beings to inhabit and perhaps adventure once
more.

name: Standing on level ground
description:
You are standing at the edge of a steep set of foothills. Looking down, you
see what appears to be a marshy, dark forest. It reeks of death and decay.
Even here, you catch its scent on the winds. From here, you can travel south
deeper into the foothills or to the west where a small pass will allow you to
climb down.

name: Mine entrance
description:
The little path here leads down toward the mines, while the worn path
continues to the west.

name: Construction site of the Harold Finkelbaum Block.
description:
A Mega-City One City Block is being constructed at this site.  A
typical block is from 100 to 1000 stories high with hundreds of
thousands inhabitants.

name: Shortcut
description:
This is a shortcut between Dracolich Plaza and the center of town.
Dracolich Plaza is to the west and the shortcut continues south.

name: The burial grounds
description:
Random tombs to unknown warriors were lain in rows as far as the eye
can see.  To your horror many of the graves are empty and desecrated.
A gap in the rows of tombs leads south and there are more graves to the
east and west.

name: Western side of Chamber
description:
You are on the western side of the main chamber overlooking a sacrificial
pit. To the north is an altar.

name: Inside a Luxurious Bedroom
description:
A peaceful feeling overtakes you.  You see a magnificent four-poster bed.
It's a double bed and there is only room for one more!  Well, what now ... ?

name: Raging hurricane.
description:
You are buffeted and knocked about by the almost godlike strength
of the raging hurricane.  It is hard to see and hear anything.
Your only thought is to seek refuge from the storm.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: Clearing
description:
You stand out in a clearing.  Mountains are all around you.  There is a
well in the middle of the clearing.  Lying against the well is a sign.  A
path leads up the mountain.  The small opening is back to the north.

name: Roaming the Astral Plane
description:
You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is somewhat disorienting, though your instincts say you are
close to home.
All exits lead off into the astral field.

name: A small path in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a narrow path leading through the deep, dark forest.  Ancient,
grey trees loom everywhere.  The path continues south and west.

name: Dark Hallway
description:
You find yourself in a very old section of the fortress.  You must be the
first person to pass through here in years.  The hallway continues south
and a door leads off to the east.

name: A narrower tunnel
description:
The tunnel becomes very narrow and you fight to squeeze your way through.
The floor seems to level off a little.

name: Darkest Caves
description:
Your light doesn't even seem to work here.  Even magical light sources seem
only to illuminate about a foot ahead of you.  You suddenly realize that the
path has descended quite a bit but you didn't notice before because of the
darkness.  You sense a great presence directly to the east.

name: Realm of the Hopeless
description:
Here you see many misguided souls who think they still live.
They search for those who killed them without warrant, and seek the
free souls of living beings to inhabit and perhaps adventure once
more.

name: In the foothills
description:
You are in a barren set of foothills. Looking around, all you see are dead
plants and boulders. From the south, you get a whiff of salty air. Barren paths
lead east, north, and south into more barren hills.

name: Inside the mine
description:
There are holes everywhere from the places that the workers blew
away the rock to get to whatever they were looking for.  A path leads
down and up.

name: Corner of Junket Way and Threep Lane
description:
There is a second-hand kneepad stall is doing a brisk business with a
group of juves on their way to school.  Junket Way goes west and Threep
Lane travels south.

name: The Altar
description:
You are standing in front of a highly and freshly bloodstained altar.
Engraved on the top of the altar is a giant spider with a human head. Looking
down from the altar you see a large sacrificial pit.

name: Ice Dragon Way
description:
Several smashed crystal statues line the Way here.  You begin to wonder
who smashed them, and with what.  The Way bends out of sight to the north
and continues south.  To the east is a courtyard.

name: The burial grounds
description:
It seems as if many of the warriors could not stop fighting even in
death.  They fight amongst each other and flail at any living being
that would wander near.

name: The Plains
description:
You are standing on the plains. This is a vast desolate place where the
wind can howl undisturbed since nothing but you bars its way. However you
are not the first to wander here. Before you somebody has left a small path.
The path looks rather bewildered and is not the kind of path to lead to
anywhere significant or important but it seems to have made up its mind to
enter the hills far away north.

name: The Lower Chambers and Tombs of the Undead
description: The stench of death is heavy in these caverns.

name: The Supreme Court
description:
You are standing inside the dock of a court.  You feel an overwhelming
sense of guilt and you want to protest your innocence!  You fear retribution
and feel yourself exposed, just like the trees in Autumn.

name: Raging hurricane.
description:
You are buffeted and knocked about by the almost godlike strength
of the raging hurricane.  It is hard to see and hear anything.
Your only thought is to seek refuge from the storm.

name: A path
description:
This path leads up the side of the mountain.  A clearing lies below you.
There is a cave opening to the west.  The path continues up the mountain.

name: Roaming the Astral Plane
description:
You find yourself floating in a field of blackness, filled with tiny tendrils
of silvery light and insubstantial shining motes of dust.  The weightlessness
of this environment is somewhat disorienting, though your instincts say you are
close to home.
All exits lead off into the astral field.

name: Torture Chamber
description:
This is a room that was once used to extract lies out of helpless victims.
The machines look unused, but could still work.

name: A small path in the deep, dark forest
description:
You are on a narrow path leading through the deep, dark forest.  Huge, ancient
trees are on all sides.  The path continues north and south.

name: Earth Chamber
description:
This is the abode of the Earth Ruler.  He decides about earthquakes,
landslides, and avalanches.  The Earth Ruler sits upon a huge marble throne
carved into the wall.

name: The Donjonkeep
description:
No souls have ever lived in this place.  The wails of slaves
and the howls of wolves are the only way you can describe the sounds
you hear.  The walls are thin and wispy.  The only light you receive
is the shimmering from the strand of the ethereal web you used to get
here.

name: Path in the mine
description:
You are deep inside the mine, and you feel very uncomfortable.  The
path continues to the east, and leads to the mineshaft to the west.

name: Before the huge tree
description:
You enter a large ring of boulders. Sheltered by this wall of stones, a small
cluster of plants have sprung up. In the center of this group of trees and
bushes is a huge gnarled tree. It appears to have been twisted and torn by
the forces of nature. It sways and moans as a strong wind from the south tears
through its old feeble branches. The hills themselves lead in all directions.

name: A narrow crack
description:
This part of the tunnel is the hardest to move through as the walls
move in to meet you.

name: Slave Cells
description:
This is the main room to the cell chambers for the slaves to be
sacrificed. You notice there are no guards around.

name: The burial grounds
description:
